title: fall harvest spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Grease and flour two 9 inch round baking pans.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach using package directions; drain.
Saute onions in margarine in skillet until onions are transparent.
Stir in stuffing mix, beaten eggs, Parmesan cheese and garlic powder. Roll into small balls.
Place on baking sheet; freeze.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until firm.
Serve warm.
May store frozen spinach balls in plastic bags in freezer and bake as needed.
Yield:
112 servings.

title: grandma molly's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients, roll into balls and dip in a mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Flatten with two fingers on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed potatoes, salt and pineapple.
Place half of mixture in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar, 16 marshmallows and half of the pecans.
Cover with remaining brown sugar.
Place remaining marshmallows and nuts on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar and salt.
Add milk and vanilla. Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle nutmeg over pie before baking.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add beaten egg to milk; mix well with yeast and sugar dissolved in water.
Cut shortening into flour with liquid to form a soft ball.
Knead gently on floured board.
Roll and cut.
Place on greased pan; brush with butter.
Let stand and rise until doubled in size.
Bake.

title: brown bread
directions: While pouring cornmeal into boiling water, stir constantly. Add salt, margarine and molasses.
After mixture has cooled, add yeast mixture, then flour.
Mix well.
Rise.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: sloppy joe casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Brown meat and add seasoning.
Mix tomato sauce, paste and water.
Layer noodles, meat and cottage cheese.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Brown ground beef, onions and bell pepper; drain.
Pour 1/3 of corn meal mixture into pan.
Put one layer of corn, a layer of ground beef and a layer of cheese.
Pour the rest of the corn meal mixture over the top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: pecan sandies or snowballs
directions: Cream together all ingredients.
Chill for 2 to 4 hours.
Roll into balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 325°.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: cranberry salad or dessert
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1 cup of juice or add water to make 1 cup.
Heat juice until boiling; pour over jello and cool.
After cool, stir in ginger ale.
Blend pineapple and cranberry sauce and fold into jello mixture.
Put in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan; chill until firm.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 of chocolate chips at low speed for 1/2 minute.
Scrape down bowl.
Beat for 2 more minutes or till smooth.
Pour into a greased and floured 13x9-inch pan.
Sprinkle the rest of the chips over batter.
Bake 40-45 minutes at 350°.

title: chewies
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to boil and remove from heat immediately. Stir in peanut butter and chow mein noodles. Drop by tablespoonfuls onto waxed paper and allow to cool. Serves 24.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Add flour, salt and soda; mix.
Add vanilla, apples and pecans.
Bake in tube pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 1 hour.
Should be brown and firm when done.

title: gran wise's vegetable relish
directions: Chop all vegetables; drain and mix all together.
Mix next ingredients together.
Dissolve good.
Let stand 15 minutes. Pour over mixed vegetables.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cranberry supreme
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Stir well.
Press into a greased 8-inch dish and chill.
Combine cranberries, sugar and water in saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in pecans and marmalade; chill.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, milk and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread over crust.
Top with cranberry mixture.
Chill 8 hours.
Yield:
9 servings.

title: dessert pizza
directions: Press cookie dough onto cookie sheet (with sides) sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar until fluffy.
Spread over cooled crust.
Arrange fruit decoratively on top.
Melt jelly (I microwave) and brush over fruit to glaze.
Cut in wedges.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: drop butter wafers
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well.
Drop the cookies from a teaspoon well apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 7 minutes or until the rims brown in a 350° oven.

title: oyster stew
directions: Melt margarine in 3-quart pot; add Texas Pete, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Mix well.
Add oysters with juice.
Simmer at medium heat until edges of oysters curl.
Add milk while stirring.
Cook at low heat for 10 minutes, stirring continuously.
Do not let milk boil!! Serves 4.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk and food coloring in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until hot.
In a bowl, mix cornstarch, sugar and egg yolks.
When milk is hot, put mixture into it.
Stir until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Peel and slice bananas.
Layer cookies, bananas and pudding.
End with cookies on top.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: norwegian apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Spread in large greased and floured pan.
Top with apple slices.
Sprinkle with mixture of 2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1 cup sugar.
Bake at 340° for 45 minutes.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Bring to boil.
Cool and add powdered sugar to thickness desired.

title: "ants on a log"
directions: Wash celery.
Cut into long strips.
Put peanut butter in middle of celery.
Place a few raisins in a row on top of peanut butter.
A good afternoon snack!

title: pizzelles
directions: Mix all ingredients well and cook on pizzelle iron.

title: fruit dressing
directions: Mix.
Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.

title: best date bars
directions: In saucepan, combine dates, sugar and water.
Cook, stirring frequently, until very thick.
Stir in walnuts; cool.
Meanwhile, sift flour, salt and soda together in a mixing bowl; add oats and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until crumbly.
Sprinkle water over mixture; stir lightly.
Pat half into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread with date mixture.
Cover with remaining oat mixture and pat lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yield:
40 bars.

title: colorful pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles, drain.
Saute onions until tender.
Mix in all ingredients.
Add seasonings to taste.
Best served at room temperature.

title: blueberry cheesecake bars
directions: Grease a 9-inch pan.
Rinse blueberries with cold water and drain.
Cut oleo into muffin mix.
Stir in nuts.
Press into bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add egg, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Spread on crust. Sprinkle with blueberries.
Sprinkle on topping from muffin mix. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Refrigerate when cool.

title: powdered sugar cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar for 10 minutes; add all ingredients.
Add red and green cake coloring for holidays!
Bake at 300° until done.

title: special squash casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together with cracker crumbs.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with crumbs, cheese and margarine. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach cream biscuit foldovers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, cook and stir onions in 1/4 cup margarine until tender; stir in spinach and cream cheese. Cook over low heat until cream cheese is melted, stirring constantly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add evaporated milk.
Then add corn, tuna (broken up), green pepper and onion.
Pour all into a buttered casserole dish to bake it, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburger, green peppers and onions.
Mix together.
Add salt, pepper and a little sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: choco-date cake
directions: Combine dates and boiling water; cool to room temperature. Stir shortening to soften; cream in sugar until fluffy.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift together cake flour, cocoa, soda and salt; add to creamed mix alternately with date mix, beating well after each addition.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice according to package directions (drain broccoli).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar, butter and peanut butter together and press dough into pan.
Melt chips and spread on top.

title: tomato puffs
directions: Slice tomato in half.
Sprinkle each half with 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Top with mixture of remaining ingredients.
Broil until browned, 2 to 3 minutes.

title: yeast bread
directions: Stir together 2 cups flour and yeast.

Heat milk, water, sugar, 2 tablespoons oil and salt over low heat only until warm, stirring to blend. Add liquid ingredients to flour-yeast mixture and beat until smooth, about 2 minutes on medium speed with electric mixer or 300 strokes by hand.
Add 1 cup flour and beat 1 minute on medium speed or 150 strokes by hand. Stir in more flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and satiny, about 8 to 10 minutes. Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rest 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put all together inside of oven for 10 minutes.
Take out and it's ready to serve.

title: light as a feather coconut cake(if you like coconut, you will like this recipe.)
directions: Cream in a large bowl the shortening, salt, sugar and egg. Sift dry ingredients, then add to mixture, alternating with milk. Add extract, and stir.
Add coconut, stir lightly, then place in two round, lightly greased cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cucumber crisps
directions: Slice cucumbers and put in jars.

title: parmesan deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves lengthwise.
Remove and mash yolks.
Add onions, mayonnaise, cheese and mustard.
Mix well.
Refill egg whites, using about 1 tablespoon of the mixture for each egg half. Refrigerate eggs until chilled.
Makes 12 deviled halves.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add flavoring.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together and sift. Add to ingredients and add 7-Up drink.
Mix well.
Pour in greased mold pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean at 350°.

title: rainy day banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Generously grease 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pans.
In a large bowl, mix cereal, flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Stir raisins into dry ingredients so that they are thoroughly coated.
Place bananas, eggs, oil and cider in blender container and process a second or two.
Or, stir in dish until blended and bananas are broken up.
Pour batter into prepared pans and bake about 45 minutes, until loaves have risen, pulled away from sides of the pan slightly and probably cracked on top.
Let cool in pans for 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool completely.
Store in tightly sealed plastic bag, not in the refrigerator.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
While cake is still hot, poke holes in it about 1-inch apart using the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour milk and caramel over cake, making sure cake is covered.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, garnish with Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath bar crumbs.
(I crush mine in food processor.)

title: chili dog pizza
directions: Combine biscuit mix and water to make a thick dough.
Roll or pat out on cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Make pizza crust thin with rim.
Spread chili over dough. Top with sliced hot dogs.
Sprinkle with cheese and onion.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: black bean soup
directions: Saute bacon; remove to paper towel.
Saute onion and bell pepper in bacon drippings or olive oil, if preferred.
When nearly done, break up and add bacon.
Meanwhile, place other ingredients into a soup pot and bring to a boil.
Add the vegetable mixture and seasonings to taste.
Return to boil, lower heat and simmer for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: In a bowl, combine dressings and cheese.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly. Cover and chill.
Serve with freshly ground black pepper, if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with crumbled Ritz crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Slice cake into 2 layers.
Make filling of cream cheese, Cool Whip, sugar and flavoring.
Spread bottom layer with filling, then top with layer of pie filling.
Top with remaining cake layer, another layer of filling and then the remaining pie filling.
Do not try to ice sides of cake, filling will not cling.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except dressing and Fritos.
Just before serving, add crushed Fritos and Catalina dressing.

title: mom's cranberry salad
directions: Add Jell-O to boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Let cool slightly.
Beat cranberry sauce.
Add to Jell-O.
Grate apples; add to mixture.
Add the chopped pecans and mix.
Let refrigerate overnight.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 1 1/2-pint baking dish.
Stir in rice, mushroom soup, milk, onion and one-half of cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot and fluffy.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Put all ingredients in crock pot. Cover and cook low 8 to 12 hours or on high for 4 to 6 hours.

title: onions
directions: Cook eggs, vinegar and sugar until thick; pour over drained onions.

title: pear honey
directions: Mix all ingredients together; cook until thick (about 2 hours).
Fill jars and seal while hot.

title: spaghetti carbonara
directions: Saute bacon, olive oil and garlic.
(Bacon should be done, but not crisp.)
Drain off fat, leaving 1 to 2 tablespoons.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Cook and drain pasta.
Pour bacon over pasta. Add cheese and stir.
Add eggs and stir until combined.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix together peaches, sugar and flour. Put into pastry-lined 10-inch deep pie pan. Mix vanilla and cream together and pour over peaches. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Mix by hand.
Spoon into large 9 x 13-inch glass dish and put 1 can Angel Flake coconut on top.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot; cook on low setting 8 to 10 hours.

title: double corn biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet. Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: black-eyed peas - dressed up
directions: Cut up tomatoes (and juice) in medium pieces; put in pot with lid.
Add chopped onion and cook until onion is done.
Add peas and cook on medium until warm.
Serve in a bowl as soup.
An easy and fast meal.
Very good in cold weather.
Serve with saltine crackers or cheese toast.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for several hours before serving.
Serve with party rye bread, crackers, etc.

title: peanut butter pudding cake
directions: Stir together flour, brown sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, peanut butter, oil and vanilla.
Spread in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Carefully pour hot water over entire top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve warm with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: husband's delight
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles; drain.
Mix sour cream and cream cheese together.
In a 2-quart baking dish, put layers of noodles, meat sauce, sour cream mixture and grated cheese, ending with grated cheese on top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: elvis' peanut butter & banana sandwich
directions: Mash the banana to a pulp. Spread the peanut butter on one slice of bread. Spread the mashed banana on the other. Gently press the two slices together. Melt the butter/margarine over medium-low heat in a small frying pan. Fry the sandwich on one side until golden brown. Flip and fry the other side. Eat by hand (this can be messy) or with knife and fork.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and pour into Pam sprayed casserole dish, approximately 9 x 11-inch.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Last 5 minutes of baking, sliced Swiss cheese can be added.

title: grand's chili dish
directions: Pour chili into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes (until bubbly hot) in a 400° oven.
Remove from oven. Sprinkle cheese on top and place chips around edge on their ends.

title: yellow party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and club soda.
Pour into containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer in time to get slushy at serving time.
Add equal amounts of ginger ale and club soda.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Use Crisco pie crust recipe. For extra flaky pastry, add extra Crisco. Bake pie crust shell in 425° oven until golden, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown tortillas in oil and set aside.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add beans, seasoning and sauce.
Simmer a few minutes.
In baking dish, arrange tortillas and meat sauce alternately.
Place cheese over top of casserole.
Bake in hot oven until Mozzarella cheese is melted.

title: grits casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off oil.
Chop up pepper, onion and celery.
Put pepper, onion and celery in a large saucepan.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Mix grits, sausage, pepper, onion and celery together.
Spread undiluted cream of mushroom soup on top of these ingredients and sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Put in 400° oven until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: hot vegetable salad
directions: Chop cabbage in very fine pieces and fry on medium using vegetable oil.
Boil potatoes for 20 minutes and cut in pieces. Cut peppers, carrots and onions in small pieces and fry, stirring for 10 minutes using butter.
Mix everything and cook on low for 5 minutes.
Add spices to taste.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift flour, spices and soda together.
Add raisins and dates. Cream sugar and shortening together thoroughly.
Add eggs and cream until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients to this mixture, alternating with applesauce, but add flour mixture first and last.
Then add chopped walnuts.
Pour into greased layer cake pans.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Cool and top with your favorite icing.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: Mix together in baking dish. Put corn flakes (crushed) on top. Pat with butter or oleo. Bake in oven at 350° about 30 minutes.

title: mexican pinwheels
directions: Mix above ingredients together well, except tortillas.
Spread mixture on tortilla.
Roll.
(Place in wet paper towel to roll.) Then roll in piece of foil.
Be sure ends of towel and foil are tucked in.
This freezes beautifully.
Need to make at least 24 hours in advance.
Cut rolls into bite size pieces to serve.
They may be dipped into picante sauce if desired.

title: raisin bran bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients. Mix dry ingredients. Combine, mixing well after each addition. Pour batter in an oiled bread pan. Bake right away at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: no crust apple pie
directions: Fill pan 3/4 full with apples.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Melt margarine.

title: "key lime" pie
directions: Mix last three ingredients and pour into pie crust. Refrigerate until time to serve.
Garnish each slice with slim twisted slice of lime.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind cranberries and oranges; stir in liquid artificial sweetener and reserved juice.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Yield:
2 cups.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 0 g, fat 0 g, calories 24.
One serving = 1/8 cup or less free food exchange.

title: baked pineapple(ideal served with ham)
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs.
Add pineapple; mix well, then put in greased casserole.
Put cubed bread on top of pineapple mixture.
Add melted butter on top of bread cubes.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: dutch corn cabbage
directions: Fry
bacon
until
crisp.
Crumble.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings.
Add water, corn and cabbage to drippings.
Cook covered about 5 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Add bacon and seasoning.
Mix lightly and serve.
Quick cooking saves the delicate flavor.

title: rosemary's muffins
directions: Mix milk, egg and shortening.
Sift other ingredients and mix with first mixture.
Do not beat.
Pour into greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked stuff potatoes
directions: Wash and bake 6 large Idaho potatoes.
Take from oven while hot, cut circle hole in potatoes.
Take a tablespoon and take out all of the potato leaving only the shell.
Mash potatoes in large bowl adding chopped celery, green pepper, onions, garlic, bacon, sausage, cheese, butter, evaporated milk, salt and pepper.
Mix until potatoes soft but little stiff.
Take soft potatoes and stuff back in potato shell.
Sprinkle top of potato with paprika. Put potatoes in baking pan and bake 20 minutes until top is brown. Serves 5 or 6.

title: southern oven "fried" chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In bowl, mix buttermilk and 1 1/2 teaspoons seasoning.
Soak chicken in buttermilk 2 hours in refrigerator.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Transfer chicken to dry mixture; coat.
Coat chicken with cooking spray; bake on a greased baking sheet 25 minutes or until golden brown and juices run clear.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bone or drain cans and put in pot on stove.
Add Veg-All, soups, salt and pepper.
Add milk until creamy.
Bring to boil.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and top with biscuits.
Bake according to biscuit package until brown.

title: green wonder salad
directions: Drain liquid from canned vegetables (liquid can be saved to use in soups and sauces). Mix all vegetables, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper in large bowl. Cover and refrigerate several hours. Salad will keep several weeks in refrigerator in tightly covered container. Yields 3 pints.

title: barbecued pecans
directions: Mix butter, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce with garlic salt.
Coat pecans with mixture.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool.
Serve as is or spread cream cheese between 2 halves.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Add all other ingredients except Ritz crackers.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 30 minutes).

title: spiced lemonade
directions: Heat water, cloves and sugar until they reach boiling point; lower heat and let it continue boiling for 2 minutes.
Cool.
Add fruit juices and enough cold water to reach the desired taste. Serve over cracked ice.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: golden banana punch
directions: Mix all of the above.
Strain juice through cheesecloth to eliminate the black specs found in the bananas.
Pour quart of mixture into a mold of your choice; freeze (this is used to decorate as well as keep the punch cold).

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut tortillas in quarters.
In a greased casserole dish, layer tortillas, chicken, olives, onions and cheeses; repeat layers. Mix chicken stock, soups and chilies together; heat.
Pour mixture over layers; top with remaining cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine flour and corn meal.
Add milk and margarine; mix. Add egg and sour cream; stir until blended.
Heat the oil in iron skillet; sprinkle with corn meal.
Pour in mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter with chocolate.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour filling into 9-inch unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: never fail fudge(microwave)
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa into medium glass bowl.
Add milk and margarine.
Cut into 4 or 5 pieces, but do not stir.
Microwave 2 to 2 1/2 minutes on High.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir to blend well.
Pour and spread into an 8 or 9-inch square buttered pan. Chill 1 hour before cutting into squares.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Combine Ricotta, Parmesan and 1 cup Mozzarella.
Stir in sausage and ziti.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole.
Pour 1/2 jar Ragu over this.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning over sauce; sprinkle 1 cup Mozzarella over all. Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake for about 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°, or until mixture is completely heated through.

title: ham and cheese delight
directions: Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Combine with all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo and powdered sugar.
Add egg yolks and egg whites. Slowly add flour.
Form into patties.
Chill, covered tightly, overnight.
Roll very thin.
Cut out.
Brush the top of each cookie with egg white (beaten egg white).
Sprinkle top with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
(I put in a salt shaker.)
Bake at 325° until very light brown.
Store in a tight container.
The thinner they are rolled, the better they are.

title: beef and barley vegetable soup
directions: Drain tomatoes and beans, reserving juice.
Add enough water to make 2 quarts.
Place liquid, meat, salt, pepper, celery tops and parsley sprigs in a large kettle. Cover and simmer 1 hour. Add barley and simmer 1 hour longer.
Add all vegetables and tomato juice and cook for at least 45 minutes.
Makes 5 quarts.

title: priest's lunch
directions: Combine all ingredients with 2 1/2 consomme cans of water in deep casserole.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: fried rice
directions: Add cold water to cooked rice; separate grains.
Add eggs to bacon.
Heat skillet on high; add oil.
Fry celery and onion until soft; add eggs and bacon and cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add rice and mix.
Add sauce made from all other ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well the crushed pretzels, oleo and 3 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely!

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Cream sugar and butter or oleo.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Wash chicken thoroughly.
Put rice in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix mushroom soup and celery soup in bowl with the milk.
Pour soup mixture over rice.
Put chicken on top of rice and soup mixture.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup over chicken.
(I put in more onions.)
Cover with foil and bake 2 hours at 350°.
Do not peek.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to directions on Jiffy meal box.

title: chicken brunswick stew
directions: Heat large Dutch oven and add bacon fat.
Fry chicken until lightly brown and add the water, tomatoes, onions, sugar and wine. Cover and bring to a simmer.
Cook for 1 1/4 hours.
Remove chicken from pot and allow to cool enough to handle.
Debone chicken and discard skin and bones.
Tear meat into small pieces and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients to the pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Add chicken and cook for another 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Blend cheese and sugar.
Add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth.
Stir in vanilla, salt and walnuts.
Spread in greased 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours, cut into small squares. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix in peanut butter with a fork until crumbly; set aside.
Beat eggs slowly, add milk to eggs.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture; stir just enough to mix.
Fill greased bread pan half full.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Drop by spoonfuls into boiling broth and cook 15 to 20 minutes with tight cover on kettle.
Do not take lid off until done.

title: payday spread
directions: Mix all together.
Add a dash of pepper.
Let stand a day or 2 before using.

title: rhubarb-pineapple custard kuchen
directions: Line
x 12-inch glass pan with crust recipe (margarine or butter,
cup sugar and egg yolks).
Cream with a spoon and add
cups flour and salt.
Mix well and pat into pan, working
up sides.	Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour
and	sprinkle
over crust.
Fill crust lined pan with chopped
rhubarb mixed with crushed, drained pineapple.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs in bowl.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and nuts; mix well.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bread tests done.
Cool slightly in pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: rich and creamy vegetable sauce
directions: Melt butter and cream.
Add vanilla extract and sugar on very low heat.
Beat with whisk while on heat.
Mixture will thicken, but it won't get too thick because it is hot.
Pour over vegetables or even fruit.

title: german chocolate cake topping
directions: Using 8 or 9-inch round layer cake pans, make and cool cake as directed on the label.
In a medium saucepan combine sugar, evaporated milk, egg yolks and shortening.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Cool 15 minutes.
Spread only between layers and on top of cake.

title: creole corn
directions: In 1 1/2 qt. casserole, combine celery, green pepper and oil. Cover.
Microwave at High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until tender.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix
ingredients
with	juice from fruit cocktail until well blended.
Place
in greased pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar over the top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: crab balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding enough bread crumbs to form mixture into a ball shape.
Deep fry until golden brown. Drain on paper towels.

title: chicken tarragon(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cut chicken into thick julienne strips.
Add tarragon to wine, let stand 30 minutes.
In skillet, melt 2 tablespoons of butter over medium heat and saute mushrooms.
Remove mushrooms from skillet and set aside.

title: chocolate peanut butter cups
directions: You will need 24 paper nut cups, 1 3/4 x 1 1/4 inches. Combine butter and peanut butter in medium bowl.
Microwave at 50% (Medium) 2 to 4 minutes, until butter melts, stirring 1 or 2 times.
Stir in crumbs and sugar.
Set aside.

title: christmas angel pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, juice and salt and cook in double boiler until thick.
Add oleo; let cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff (2 whites); add flour and milk.
Mix well.
Put in baked pie shell.
Use 2 egg whites for topping.
Beat until stiff.
Top pie and brown.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken tostadas
directions: Toss chicken with salsa.
Spread shells with cream cheese. Top with chicken mixture, lettuce, tomato and cheese.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Cut potatoes into slices; place on greased pan. In bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Spread evenly over potatoes.

title: dottie's dirt salad
directions: Grind Oreo cookies in blender.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar and set aside.
Mix together milk and instant vanilla pudding; set aside.
Mix together Cool Whip and vanilla and add to pudding mixture.
After combining the pudding mixture with Cool Whip mixture, fold in cream cheese mixture.

title: yellow velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Add eggs, oil, buttermilk, vanilla and yellow coloring.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes in an oblong pan.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake according to directions.
After making cake, mix the jello.
Use 1 cup boiling water to dissolve both large packages of jello.
Dissolve frozen strawberries in jello.
Mix the pudding.

title: veal parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Parmesan.
Dip cutlet in beaten egg, then in crumbs.
Fry quickly, until golden brown. Drain.
Place meat on ovenproof platter.
Arrange cheese slices on each cutlet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Saute onions and garlic in 1 tablespoon oil.
Stir in oregano and tomato sauce.
Heat to boiling, then simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over meat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Note:
This cake has no oil or eggs!

title: pineapple delight
directions: In large bowl, add 1 bag of miniature marshmallows, 1 carton heavy whipping cream and 2 cans crushed pineapple.
Strain pineapple prior to adding to mixture.
Mix ingredients until well blended.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Stir prior to serving.

title: party chicken and shrimp
directions: In 12-inch skillet, over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion until tender, stirring occasionally.
Remove onion.
In drippings, cook chicken breast halves until browned on both sides.
Into skillet with chicken, measure 3 tablespoons minced parsley; stir in onion, tomato sauce, wine, water, salt, basil and pepper.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add shrimp, cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Skim off fat from liquid in skillet.
Spoon onto platter.
Sprinkle with remaining parsley.
Makes 6 servings.

title: soft shell tacos
directions: In a bowl mix flour, baking powder and salt; cut in the shortening.
Add warm water a little at a time to form a soft dough.
Cover and let rest 1 hour.
Meanwhile, fry ground beef with onion and drain.
Add to ground beef the refried beans, garlic powder and cumin; simmer for about 5 minutes.
After dough has set for 1 hour, pinch off a walnut size chunk of dough and roll out on a lightly floured surface to a very thin circle. Place 1/4 cup filling on half or circle.
Fold dough in half and press tightly around edges, making a pocket.
Deep fry immediately until golden brown.
Reopen shell and fill with cheese, lettuce and tomatoes.
Top with taco sauce and sour cream, if desired.

title: creamed corn
directions: Put the corn and milk in a small saucepan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring with a fork every once in a while, until milk is almost completely reduced (about 15 minutes). Add water and cook another 10 minutes until liquid has reduced to just below the surface of corn.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and salt.
Process 3/4 cup of the kernels in a food processor, then stir the puree back in with the kernels.
Add the butter, if desired.

title: you know who's "millionaires"
directions: Put Kisses and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans and stir to blend.
Drop by teaspoonful on waxed paper and cool in refrigerator until ready to dip.
Melt milk chocolate morsels and paraffin together in heavy saucepan on low heat.
Be very careful not to get mixture too hot as it can flame.
Remove pecan clusters from refrigerator. Working quickly, dip in chocolate and place on waxed paper.
These are great and they taste just like the expensive ones.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Add water to slightly beaten egg white.
Add sugar, spices and salt to egg mixture.
Let stand until sugar is dissolved, about 15 minutes.
Dip nuts in mixture.
Spread on cookie sheet with flat side down.
Bake in 250° oven until golden brown, about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Use all brown sugar but 1 cup.
Add milk; boil until it forms hard ball in cold water.
Remove from burner.
Add butter and vanilla.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Beat until thick.
Add peanuts.
Pour into 10 x 10-inch pan.

title: turkey dressing
directions: Fry green peppers, celery and onion with sausage.
Add rest of recipe to mixture and 2 tablespoons sage.
Add broth and mix.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: In baking dish, mix potatoes, eggs, sugar, 1 stick melted butter and vanilla.
Mix and sprinkle on top the coconut, brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1 stick of melted butter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: great biscuits(you gotta try these to believe them!)
directions: Break egg up with a fork in a measuring cup. Fill cup with milk.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and shortening by "hand" in bowl. Add egg/milk mixture. Mix lightly with fingers.
Lightly flour board. Place mixture on board and gently knead, mixing in enough flour to be able to roll out 1-inch thick.
Cut and bake at 400° about 9 to 10 minutes.

title: jenny's cake
directions: Prepare favorite yellow cake.
Blend cream cheese, dry pudding and a small amount of milk to the consistency of frosting.
Frost cake.
Spread pineapple over frosting.
Cover with Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts, coconut and cherries.

title: spinach salad(makes 8 servings)
directions: In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain, reserving 1/4 cup drippings.
Crumble bacon; set aside.

title: cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup of dry cake mix.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Press into bottom and sides of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Mixture may be crumbly.)

title: rhubarb deep dish dessert
directions: Put rhubarb, 2 cups sugar, egg, 3 tablespoons milk, 1/4 cup flour and nutmeg in a large casserole.

title: dinette cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients. Blend well; then beat 2 minutes.
Bake in a buttered pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven french fries
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Coat potatoes in bowl with oil. Season with Lawry's seasoned salt.
Place in disposal pan; pour enough oil in pan to cover bottom.
Place in 400° oven or on top of outside grill where you bake potatoes on top rack.
Keep checking potatoes and stir them.
Done when golden brown and tender.

title: apple cider slaw
directions: In large bowl, toss together green and red cabbage, cucumbers, onions and corn.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, pour over the cabbage mixture and toss well.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: texas casserole
directions: Brown meat, pepper and onion in shortening.
Add tomatoes, salt and all spices.
Simmer 15 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking. Heat corn and add rice and corn to meat mixture.
Pour into 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Add oregano to taste.
Cut cheese into chunks and add to sausage and melt.
After the mixture has melted, spread mixture on rye bread.
These can be made ahead of time and frozen.
You can also divide the recipe in half.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix flour, oleo (softened) and nut meats.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Remove and mix with a fork and press back in pan and cool.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick and clear.
Add food coloring and jello; let cool.
Put strawberries in cooled pie crust; spoon filling over berries.
Chill before serving and add whipped cream.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, but mix catsup last.

title: chocolate pound cake *
directions: Put in a large bowl and beat sugar, margarine and Crisco for 10 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, without opening oven door, then check.

title: soy pork
directions: Place pork loin into large baking dish. Add water and soy sauce. Garnish top of loin with salt, garlic powder, hot peppers and parsley leaves. Bake at 350° for approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Serve immediately.

title: oat and raisin bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients and raisins in a large bowl.
In another bowl, blend remaining ingredients.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen muffins.

title: fish stew
directions: Cook salt pork in a Dutch oven over low heat for 20 minutes or until most of the fat is rendered.
Add onion.
Cook over medium heat until onion is tender and pork is brown.
Add potatoes and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add fish, soup, milk, Worcestershire sauce and egg. Continue cooking until potatoes are tender and soup is heated through.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buffalo chips
directions: In a large bowl, cream together butter, brown sugar and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, flour, baking powder, baking soda and vanilla; mix well after each addition.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.

title: mashed potatoes(can be frozen)
directions: Cook potatoes for mashing.
Whip potatoes.
Add sour cream, cheese, butter, pepper and salt.
Place in baking dish; freeze. Remove from freezer.
May thaw some and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Whip up in dish and serve.

title: white chocolate cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening. Gradually add sugars, beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg; mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Blend in vanilla.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Drop by heaping tablespoons about 3-inches apart on ungreased cooking sheets.	Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Let stand a few minutes before removing to a wire rack to cool.
Yield:
About 2 1/2 dozen.

title: easy beer bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar and beer; stir just until ingredients are moistened.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Brush with melted butter. Remove bread from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: jade salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling.
Add jello and stir to dissolve. Let cool.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a 325° oven until set or slightly brown on top.

title: rocky road sheet cake
directions: Sift into bowl, flour, salt, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to boil, cold water, oil and oleo.
Pour over dry ingredients; beat well and add buttermilk, soda and eggs and beat again.
Bake on cookie sheet, 15 x 10 3/4-inch at 400° for about 18 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a 2-quart heavy saucepan, cook sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook over medium flame, stirring constantly until it spins a fine thread (240°).
Add peanuts and salt and cook about 10 minutes more, stirring occasionally.
Remove from flame and stir in butter or margarine and soda.
Mix well.
Pour onto a greased shallow pan or hard surface and spread or pull thin.
When cold, break into small pieces.
Makes about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, eggs, Cheddar cheese, soup and onion. Cook broccoli in microwave (drain), mix with remaining ingredients. Saute crackers in butter until lightly brown, then cover top of casserole (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix chuck, garlic salt, crumbs and egg.
Form into small meatballs.
Boil 3/4 cup grape jelly with the chili sauce.
Drop meatballs into sauce and simmer 45 minutes.

title: artichoke crab dip
directions: Combine mayonnaise and cheese.
Stir in crab and artichokes. Place in a glass baking dish and chill overnight.
To serve hot, bake in preheated 350 degree oven until bubbling, about 30 minutes. Place in a chafing dish and serve with chips.

title: delicate pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Prepare cake as directed on package.
Divide batter evenly in pans.
Bake for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frankfurter frittata
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add frankfurters and cook until browned, about 4 to 5 minutes.
Add eggs, cheese and parsley.
Cook until eggs are set.
Turn over to brown other side.
Serve with potato salad or cole slaw.

title: bbq wieners
directions: Cut wieners & add ingredients. Simmer a few minutes.

title: zucchini provencale
directions: Wash zucchini.
Do not remove skin.
Cut into small slices and cook in small amount of water until tender, about 5 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms carefully; dry with absorbent paper.
With a sharp knife, remove stem.
Chop stems, finely.
In a frying pan combine stems and garlic in one tablespoon butter.
Cook until soft.
Remove to a bowl.
Blend in bread crumbs, salt and pepper. Stuff caps with stem crumb mixture or Italian sausage.
Saute in remaining butter slowly for 10 minutes.
Drain on absorbent paper. Serve immediately.
Cook longer if you use sausage.

title: regal chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Toss gently.
Mix mayonnaise or salad dressing and salt.
Fold in whipping cream or Cool Whip. Add to chicken mixture.
Chill.
To garnish, serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: purple sherbet punch
directions: Make 2 quarts fresh tea.
Start the punch with the tea.
Add the Hawaiian Punch, grape Kool-Aid, sugar and water to the tea. Stir good.
Add sugar according to your desire.
Put in refrigerator until cool.
Just before serving, add your sherbet, stir very little.
Ready to serve.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Mix flour, 2 cups sugar, oil, eggs, baking powder and orange juice together.
Blend until smooth.
Pour half into greased tube or Bundt cake pan.
Put half the apples on top of cake batter. Mix cinnamon and 5 tablespoons sugar; sprinkle half on top of apples.
Pour in the rest of batter and repeat layers of apples and cinnamon-sugar.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water.
Drain.
Mix oil, Parmesan cheese and eggs with spaghetti to form pie crust.
Saute green peppers and onions with margarine; mix with sour cream and place on top of pie crust.
Cook meat (can use all ground meat) and drain. Mix spices (1 package) with the tomato paste (or you may use sauce), water and meat.
Place on top of sour cream.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and bake another 5 minutes to melt. This will freeze well.
Thaw thoroughly prior to baking.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine cider and sugar.
Mix well.
Add spices and juices. Let simmer at low heat.

title: easy chili con queso dip
directions: Drain tomatoes; add to onions, garlic and peppers.
Simmer in saucepan for 1 hour.
Add cheese; stir until cheese melts.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage.
Mix in Velveeta cheese, oregano, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce; freeze.
Put in plastic bags.
When ready to eat, bake at 350° for 10 minutes each side or butter each side of sandwich and toast in skillet.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: In pan, bring to a boil margarine, cocoa and water.
In another pan (preferably a large bowl), mix sour cream, eggs and baking powder.
Add the two mixtures together and add the flour, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Place into large (16 x 12-inch) sheet cake pan (1 inch deep).
Bake for 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven. After this bakes, in a pot add:

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour into baking dish. Melt margarine and coat cracker crumbs well.
Spread crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes until vegetables are tender, cheese melted and topping brown.

title: ruth's chicken dressing
directions: Boil chicken in water and salt until comes off bones.
Remove from pot; discard bones and skin.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup with broth the chicken was cooked in.
Add everything except biscuits, eggs and cornbread.
Mix well; crumble breads and mix into broth.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Mix chicken into dressing; pour into large pan sprayed with Pam.
Stir in 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Sprinkle paprika on top and bake in oven at 450° until done and lightly brown.
Serve with giblet gravy made from giblets, cream of chicken soup, 1 cup of dressing mixture and 2 boiled eggs, chopped.

title: special baked beans
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper with butter.
Brown the hamburger meat and drain.
Mix the ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar, mustard and pepper (salt is optional).
Drain the pork and beans and add the rest of the ingredients.
Top with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for an hour or little longer.

title: le blanc's barbecued pecans
directions: Place pecans in a shallow baking pan, spread out evenly. In a small
saucepan,
mix butter and spices.
Pour butter over pecans and stir until well coated.
Place pan of pecans on slow fire on barbecue
pit;
roast slowly 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally, until crisp and lightly browned.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large bowl and mix well to coat with pie filling.
Keeps well.
Pie filling keeps fruit from turning brown.
Other fruits (fresh) may be added to or substituted for.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: 7-up jello salad
directions: Bring water to boil.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows.
Stir over low heat or medium heat until dissolved.
Pour over jello. Stir until well mixed and jello is dissolved.
Add 7-Up or Sprite and crushed pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: fast and easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter, and cream.
Cook to soft ball stage. Take off stove and let cool a minute.
Add peanut butter chips, and beat until thick.
Pour into a buttered pan.
Let cool, then cut.

title: andy's granny salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: one egg cake
directions: Sift flour. Add baking powder and salt; sift together.
Cream butter thoroughly. Add sugar; add milk, vanilla and egg. Mix well. Bake at 375° until toothpick inserted in cake comes out clean.

title: my friend's idea
directions: Layer zucchini, tomatoes, onion, bread crumbs and cheese in a baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Slice large onions into medium-thick slices.
Soak slices in sweet milk for at least 1 hour.
Make batter just before cooking.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift enriched all-purpose flour and measure.
Resift 3 times with soda, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture appears like coarse meal.
Soften yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add yeast and buttermilk in center of flour mixture. Stir until all flour is moistened.
Cover with heavy plate and/or wrap in plastic and store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: quick turkey divan
directions: Put broccoli in small amount of water and simmer 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.
Arrange turkey in greased 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Top turkey with broccoli.
Arrange cheese slices over broccoli.
Combine milk and soup.
Pour over all.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Strew onion rings over top. Bake another 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: congealed salad
directions: Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Bring to boil and add jello.
Mix in crushed pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Pour half into glass serving dish and let partially gel. (Leave other half out of refrigerator so it will spread easier later.)
Spread sour cream over gelled salad, then add the remaining mixture on top of the sour cream.

title: mom's chestnut stuffing
directions: Toss all ingredients together and stuff.

title: blueberry nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Spray bread pan.
Pour into bread pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan to cooling rack.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.
Store in Saran Wrap.

title: seafood pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Slice vegetables in bite-sizes.
Combine with noodles.
In medium bowl, combine mayo, Italian dressing and dill weed until blended.
Pour into noodle mixture and stir until well blended.
Refrigerate.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in salted boiling water.
Make sauce of butter, milk, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until thickens.
Cut Velveeta up in pieces.
Add Velveeta to white sauce; continue stirring until all cheese is melted.
Remove from burner.
In greased casserole dish, put in macaroni.
Pour over cheese sauce.
Mix them together.
Sprinkle grated (shredded) cheese on top, then sprinkle bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Add all ingredients in a small saucepan.
Heat over low to moderate heat stirring constantly.
Sauce will thicken as it heats.
Stir vigorously.
Remove from heat when desired consistency is reached.

title: pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Stir together 1 slightly beaten egg, pumpkin, 1/3 cup sugar and pie spice.
Spread over bottom of pie shell.
Combine 2 eggs (beaten), corn syrup, 1/2 cup sugar, butter and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spoon over pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: easy cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip; blend well.
Spoon in crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: onion fried potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into 1-inch wedges.
Peel onions and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add oil and potatoes; cook for approximately 10 minutes.
Add onions, salt and pepper.
Cook until potatoes are tender and golden brown.

title: canned green beans
directions: This requires no pressure cooker.
Boil 30 minutes.
Put into jars and seal.
Cook as fresh green beans when opened with favorite seasonings.
Tastes like freshly cooked green beans.

title: carrot soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over moderate heat.
Stir in onion; cook 5 minutes.
Add carrots, chicken stock, tomato paste and rice and simmer gently for 30 minutes.
Puree soup in blender; season with salt and pepper and stir in cream.
Before serving, reheat soup on low heat; bring to a simmer.
Remove pan from heat; stir in additional tablespoon of soft butter.
Garnish with carrot curls if desired.

title: hershey's deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixer bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water (the batter will be thin and smells like hot chocolate).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or 1 (9 x 13-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers, 35 to 40 minutes for 9 x 13-inch pan or until cake tester put in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pan(s) and cool completely.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: my favorite punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl.
Add 2 trays of small ice cubes.

title: 5 pound candy
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in a saucepan, stirring well.
Cook to 240°, using a candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat with a mixer until it forms peaks.
Pour into a buttered pan.

title: ...a new twist on an old oat...
directions: Put oatmeal, water and raisins in medium size saucepan.
Heat over medium-high flame for about 1 minute.
Sprinkle in allspice and stir, cooking another 3 to 5 minutes, until it reaches desired consistency.
Remove from heat and stir in fried apples.
(The Lucky Leaf brand of fried apples comes with a heavy sweet syrup; no sugar may be needed, depending on your taste.)
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: instant cocoa
directions: Mix well in large container.
Store in airtight container. Use 1/3 cup for a cup of hot water.
Recipe makes a lot.
Can be halved.

title: aunt lucy's old fashioned sugared parsnips
directions: Cook parsnips with skins on until tender. Peel them and slice lengthwise.
Season with salt, pepper and spices.
Dip fully into butter and then into flour. Be sure to cover each piece.
Sprinkle with sugar. Fry in butter until a rich golden brown.

title: coconut pie
directions: Bring to a boil milk, sugar, flour and egg yolks (beaten). Stir constantly until mixture is thick.
Remove from heat and add coconut, butter and vanilla.
Put in a baked pie crust and add meringue, then sprinkle with coconut on top and brown in oven.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk until fluffy. Add Cool Whip and place in pie shell.
Freeze for 4 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onions.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 1 to 2 hours. Serve with grated cheese and chips.

title: bugs on a log(kids)
directions: Clean and cut celery into sticks.
Fill with peanut butter or cream cheese.
Top with raisins.

title: toll house cookies
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, except morsels and nuts).
Stir by hand until well blended.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts. Drop dough by rounded teaspoons about 2-inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 9 minutes until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from cookie sheet.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook pasta as directed on box; cool.
Cook vegetables as directed on package; cool.
Mix pasta, vegetables, cucumber and tomato with mayonnaise.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving.

title: quiche
directions: Layer onions, bacon and cheeses in pie shells.
Mix eggs, milk, parsley and salt and pepper.
Pour over the completed layered quiche.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: delicious potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: stuffed calamari
directions: In saucepan, combine garlic and oil; cook until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add salt and red pepper flakes.

title: low-fat berry bavarian
directions: Mix jello.
Stir topping.
Chill. Garnish with berries and Cool Whip.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat dough into lightly greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Make Orange Sauce.
Put crust on serving plate.
Blend cream cheese and whipped topping.
Spread this over crust.
Orange fruit over cheese mixture.
Spoon Orange Sauce over fruit.
Refrigerate.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger, drain then cool.
Chop vegetables.
Crush nacho cheese chips.
Add all together with Ranch dressing in large bowl.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Chop cabbage, celery, onion and mango; mix remaining ingredients.
Put in a tight container and let stand 12 hours before serving.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Boil pineapple and sugar 2 minutes. While cake is hot, poke holes in it and pour hot pineapple mixture over it.
Make vanilla pudding according to directions on package.
Add sour cream and pudding and spread on cool cake.
Top with Cool Whip, coconut and nuts.
Serves 16.

title: five-spice snapper
directions: Mix all ingredients except red snapper fillets.
In a preheated broiler, place fish on a broiler pan.
Brush or spoon a little of the five-spice mixture over fillets.
Turn and do the same to the underside.
Broil fish 6 inches from source of heat, basting with sauce occasionally during the 15 to 20 minute cooking time.
Do not turn fish.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: sicilian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with 4 tablespoons cheese, then flour, salt and pepper to taste.
In skillet, cook chicken in oil over medium heat until done.
Remove chicken to dish.

title: dumplings
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Beat the egg well and add the milk.
Combine the two mixtures by stirring until smooth. Drop by small spoonful into boiling meat or chicken broth.

title: hawaiian cream cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix as directed on box.
Cool and split in half; freeze extra half of cake.
Beat together the cheese, vanilla pudding and milk; spread on half cake.
Drain pineapple and spread on cheese mix.
Spread Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: pecan ball
directions: Mix all together and roll out in a ball.
Set in refrigerator 1 to 2 hours.

title: apple pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt and sage; brown slowly in hot skillet.
Place in baking dish.
Pare, core and slice apples and arrange on chops.
Pour molasses over them.
Add flour to fat in skillet; brown it, stirring constantly.
Add water, stir until it boils.
Add vinegar and raisins.
Pour over chops and apples. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Store in a tightly covered plastic container.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Boil the last 5 ingredients and pour hot over cabbage.
Store covered in refrigerator.
Keeps crisp for 2 weeks.

title: apricot jellied salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 3 cups boiling water.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Add 1 cup drained pineapple (save juice).
Let stand in refrigerator until pretty well set.
Add marshmallows, bananas, pecans and drained oranges.
Set aside until firm.

title: baked brisket
directions: Place brisket in large piece of foil or in a cooking bag. Sprinkle generously with liquid smoke, celery salt, onion salt and garlic salt.
Wrap well and put into a crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.
Serve warm with the following sauce.

title: angel hair pasta with chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast into 1 inch cubes.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in medium skillet over medium heat; add chicken.
Cook, stirring, until chicken is cooked through, about 5 minutes; drain.
Heat remaining oil in same skillet; add carrots.
Cook for 4 minutes stirring occasionally.
Add broccoli and garlic to skillet; cook for 2 minutes longer.
Add chicken broth, basil and cheese to skillet; stir to combine.
Last add chicken to mixture;
reduce heat and simmer for 4 minutes.
Pour chicken mixture over angel hair pasta.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a non-metallic bowl with wooden spoon, combine yeast with milk.
Stir until yeast has dissolved.
Add sugar and flour.
Set aside on counter.
(Proceed with cake recipe.)

title: baked indian pudding
directions: Scald milk and gradually stir in cornmeal.
Stir until thick and cook in a double boiler for 15 minutes.
Mix together sugar, molasses, salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Add to the cornmeal and stir until blended.
Add butter, egg and vanilla.
Pour into a greased baking dish and bake in a moderate oven for 1 hour.
Serve with a dash of Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: purple cows
directions: For each person, place a jumbo scoop of vanilla ice cream in a glass.
Fill glass with grape juice.
Mix well.
Serve with straws.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole(like a souffle, but not as fluffy)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add other ingredients except broccoli.
Beat well.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.
Add broccoli to the egg mixture. Mix and pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes.

title: candy sweet potatoes
directions: Peel sweet potatoes and place in casserole dish.
Mix other ingredients and bake at 400° for 20 minutes, basting frequently.

title: easy oven baked stew
directions: Combine ingredients as listed in a roaster pan.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Don't stir but can be lifted with cake turner after 2 hours.
Meat browns as it cooks.
Add mushrooms 1/2 hour before serving.

title: ooey gooey stuffed cupcakes
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.
Line 1 12-cup muffin tin with 12 paper muffin-tin liners and place 4 paper muffin-tin liners inside another muffin tin.
Add 2 tablespoons of water to each of the paperless muffin wells.
In the bowl of an electric mixer, combine the flour, sugar, cocoa powder, baking soda, and salt.
Add the egg, butter, buttermilk, and vanilla, adding the hot water last.
Beat with an electric mixer until smooth.
Divide the batter evenly among the paper muffin-tin liners.
In a small bowl, beat the cream cheese with the sugar.
Fold in the chocolate chips and coconut.
Drop the cream cheese mixture into the center of the cupcakes.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes, until the cupcakes rise and a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean. Remove from the oven and transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Drizzle chocolate sauce, the recipe of which follows, over cupcakes when serving.

title: st. paul's rice
directions: Brown sausage and drain well. Saute vegetables until tender. Bring rice, water and soup mix to a boil.
Boil for 7 minutes. Mix everything together in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: grilled chicken
directions: Place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish or heavy-duty zip top plastic bag.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients.
Pour marinade over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours, turning occasionally.

title: quick chili supper(makes a little meat go a long way)
directions: Fry ground beef and onion in pan until lightly browned.
Drain off all fat.
Add 1 cup of water or bean and tomato liquid to beef mixture.
Cook, covered, about 20 minutes until macaroni is tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add more water during cooking if necessary.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Boil cabbage leaves so they are easy to handle.
Then roll mixture in the cabbage leaves.
Place rolls on suet or fat off the steak.
Cover with water and boil for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad #3
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Ritz crackers, cheese and almonds.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Top with crackers and cheese.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 2 eggs; pat in pan.
Then mix 2 eggs, powdered sugar and pecans; pour on top.
Bake for 50 minutes or until golden brown at 350°.

title: spicy apple drink
directions: Combine cider, brown sugar, cinnamon, cloves, lemon, mace, and nutmeg in two- quart glass measure; stir until brown sugar is dissolved. Place in microwave oven. Cook on high for 10 minutes. Strain into 4 mugs. Garnish with orange slices before serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: antonnio's crock pot spaghetti
directions: Brown sirloin in skillet.
Drain tomatoes. Combine all ingredients in crock pot.
Simmer for 6 to 8 hours.
Cook vermicelli noodles until tender.
Serve sauce over noodles, sprinkled with parmesan cheese, with French or Italian bread on the side.

title: lemon cool whip cookies
directions: Beat egg at high speed or by hand until fluffy.
Add Cool Whip and blend well.
Fold in cake mix until blended.
Roll in walnut size balls.
Roll balls in sifted confectioners sugar. Place on well-greased cookie sheet an inch apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while warm with spatula. Makes about 3 dozen.
These freeze very well.
(Any flavor of box cake mix may be used.)

title: zucchini salad(another way to use up those zucchini.)
directions: Mix the onion soup mix and wine vinegar and set aside.
Mix all ingredients and let chill 4 to 6 hours before serving.

title: sweet and spicy pork tenderloin
directions: In a small bowl, combine tarragon, thyme, peppers and salt. Blend well.
Brush both sides of each pork tenderloin piece with margarine. Sprinkle both sides with seasoning mixture.

title: deer pepperoni
directions: Mix meat and Tender Quick meat cure.
Refrigerate overnight. Mix all other ingredients into the meat.
Mix well.
Roll in 3 to 4-inch rolls.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 250° to 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Turn rolls every 30 minutes.
Makes 4 rolls.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Use greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Drain shrimp.
Mix all the ingredients together.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked fudge virginia's tea room dessert
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add melted butter.
Sift flour and cocoa together and add to mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Set in a pan of hot water and bake at 325° for 45 minutes to an hour.
Serve warm with scoop of ice cream and garnish with a cherry.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: clam namasu
directions: Prepare cucumbers as in namasu by slicing thin (or julienne) and squeezing out excess water (do not salt).
Combine all ingredients; chill overnight.
Serve over cold somen noodles or as a side dish.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and oil.
Blend with veggies.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Stir well before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish; place a layer of potatoes and then layer with each of remaining ingredients.
Pour 1/2 cup of milk over last layer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream(basic vanilla)
directions: Scald
milk;
add sugar and salt to milk and stir until both are
well
dissolved.
Add cream;
stir in vanilla.
Let mixture cool.
Churn in ice cream freezer.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: fiesta banana cake
directions: Stir shortening just to soften.
Sift in dry ingredients.
Add the bananas and 1/4 of the milk and mix until all flour is dampened.
Then beat 300 strokes by hand or 2 minutes in mixer at a low speed.
Add eggs, nuts and remaining milk.
Beat 150 strokes by hand or 1 minute by mixer at a low speed.
Turn batter into pans.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Cool cake in pans on rack for 5 minutes.
Then loosen from sides with spatula; turn out, remove paper and turn right side up on racks to cool before frosting or serving.

title: pumpkin milk shakes
directions: Shake together all ingredients.
Makes 2 glasses.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale and chill.
(Very good to freeze until "slushy.")
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: sweet potato yams
directions: Peel and cut pototoes into 2-inch slices.
Put in saucepan with enough water to cover potatoes; add salt.
Cook until half done; drain potatoes.
Melt butter in microwave 1 minute.
Then mix sugar, cinnamon and milk into butter.
Pour over potatoes; bake at 400° until tender.
Remove from oven and put marshmallows on top. Put back in oven until marshmallows are golden brown.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice in chicken stock if you have it from chicken.
Let cool.
Dice chicken fairly course.
Chop onion fine.
Drain canned vegetables.
In a large bowl, lightly combine all ingredients except cheese.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake in a 350° oven until lightly brown, approximately 30 minutes.

title: charlotte's dessert
directions: Mix vanilla wafers and butter, press in 9 x 9-inch pan.
Save a few crumbs, for topping.
Refrigerate.
Soften ice cream, spread over crumb mixture, put in freezer.
Melt 1/2 cup butter and chocolate over low heat, beat egg yolks and add to chocolate.
Add sugar and vanilla, mix well, and cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
When chocolate mixture is cool, fold in egg whites and nuts.
Put on top of ice cream, sprinkle with reserved crumbs; return to freezer.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients. Batter should be thick. Spoon by rounded teaspoon fulls into hot grease. Fry until golden brown.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown celery and onions in butter.
Add hamburger balls and brown.
Take hamburger balls out when done; add rest of ingredients and cook slow for 30 minutes.
Place hamburger balls in sauce and simmer 45 minutes more.

title: hawaiian dessert
directions: Make cake as directed on package.
Pour into 2 greased 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes or until done. Cool completely.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix beans, taco mix and 1/2 taco sauce together.
Spread in a dish.
Cover with the sour cream.
Layer the hamburger, the cheese, the lettuce, tomatoes and the olives.
Spread the other 1/2 of the taco sauce on top.

title: artichoke-chilli dip
directions: Combine artichoke hearts, chopped peppers, cheese and mayo. Turn mixture into an 8-inch round baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or heated through.
Serve warm with chips and breadsticks.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli according to package and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add garlic and soup.
Add cheese until it melts.
Stir in broccoli.
Serve hot.

title: party shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix until smooth.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Best if made a day ahead.
Serve with chips or crackers.
Serves 18 to 20.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Let macaroni cool, then mix all other ingredients well.
Chill until serving time.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Stir to soften the shortening.
Gradually add sugar, creaming until light.
Add eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce, beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into wax paper lined 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove to cooling rack.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, garlic and onion in skillet.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, puree, spaghetti sauce and all spices.
Simmer for 30 minutes after it boils.
Boil lasagna until almost done. Drain.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with 1/2 of beef mixture.
Lay noodles on top until entirely covered.
Make 2 layers.
Sprinkle with 1/2 Mozzarella and all the Parmesan.
Top with remaining beef mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mayonnaise dressing
directions: Dip out about 4 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Add ingredients to the jar of mayonnaise.
Stir well.
Great for potato salad and sandwiches.

title: chocolate-applesauce bars
directions: Melt chocolate and fat together over hot water.
Cool.
Blend in sugar, eggs and applesauce.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Add to mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Spread batter in 2 greased 8-inch cake pans, or one large.
Bake in oven 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Tops may be lightly dusted with confectioners sugar if desired.
Keeps well.

title: ice cream sundae
directions: Crush 26 Oreos in blender.
Add 1/3 cup butter.
Pat in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass pan and freeze 20 minutes.

title: triple orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; stir in orange juice until thawed.
Stir in undrained pineapple.
Chill until partially set (consistency of unbeaten egg whites).
Fold in oranges.
Pour in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until almost firm.
Beat whipping cream to soft peaks; set aside.
Beat pudding mix and milk until smooth (1 to 2 minutes).
Fold in whipping cream.
Spread over gelatin.
Chill 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
You can garnish with additional oranges.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Mix together eggs, cottage cheese, flour and Cheddar cheese.
Pour over spinach.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamed corn chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (175°C).
Mix corn, green onion, milk, egg white and flour in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place chicken over mixture and sprinkle with seasoning and paprika.
Cover with bread crumbs and bake 1 hour and 20 minutes, until chicken is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add broccoli and simmer 15 minutes.
Add garlic cheese, Accent and mushrooms.
Pour into baking dish.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pistachio pudding, Cool Whip, marshmallows, pineapple and pecans together.
Top with cherries.

title: pineapple cooler
directions: Bake cake as directed on box and cool.
Mix 1 1/2 cups of milk with vanilla pudding.
In separate bowl, mix cream cheese and 1/2 cup of milk.
Beat until smooth.
Then combine pudding mixture and cream cheese mixture in either bowl.
Stir in drained, crushed pineapple.
Top cake with mixture, then top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: instant clear jell ice cream
directions: Place the first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; mix.
In small bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Beat all well.
Pour in freezer.

title: strawberry pie(shoney's style)
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until it becomes clear, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O, almond flavoring and red food coloring.
Cool to touch.
Stir in strawberries and spoon into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: Melt margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Place Crispix cereal and peanuts in a paper bag. Pour melted mixture over cereal and shake well. Pour powdered sugar in bag and shake well again.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix soup, oil, sugar and vinegar.
Add carrots, bell pepper and onion.
Cover and let set overnight.

title: mexican garbage
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir and refrigerate.
Serve with chips.

title: boiled fresh pork shoulder with cabbage
directions: Place pork shoulder in soup pot and cover with boiling water. When water returns to boil, reduce heat and simmer about 2 hours or until done.
Check after 1 1/2 hours.
If the small bone located at the shank end pulls loose easily, the meat is usually cooked.
Trim meat and remove excess fat.
Trim cabbage and cut in wedges.
Place in stock pot.
Pour boiling water and shoulder stock mixture (half and half) over cabbage and cover.
Cook for 7 to 10 minutes or until cabbage is tender.
Drain and serve.

title: chocolate syrup
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, hot water and salt.
Boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Brown together hamburger, green pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve with shredded cheese, sour cream or taco chips.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chicken soup
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and stir until dissolved. Add other ingredients and cook until bubbly.
Makes 4 cups, 130 calories each.
