(Broccoli may be used instead of chicken to make cream of broccoli soup.)

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to dry ingredients and stir only until moistened.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese, put in large bowl and let stand, covered, 8 hours or overnight.
Melt margarine and pour over cheese.
Work together by hand.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add enough of 1/2 cup water to make a rather stiff dough, mixing with hands.
Press onto slightly greased cookie sheet with a cookie press, using the star shape.
Cut into desired lengths.
Bake in preheated 325° oven. Check at 10 minutes; bottom of straw will be very lightly browned when done.
Ovens vary so cooking time will need to be adjusted accordingly.
May take 15 to 20 minutes to bake, depending on oven used.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix and bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Combine and mix first five ingredients.
Then add the rest. Mix well.
Refrigerate in covered bowl.
Set overnight before using.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Dough will keep for 1 month refrigerated.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: You will need foil cupcake liners.
Mix all ingredients, except pie filling and wafers, in bowl until creamy.
Place liners on cookie sheet or in cupcake pans.
Place one vanilla wafer, face up, in each liner.
Add one heaping spoonful of batter to each.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flavorings.
Add baking soda to flour.
Alternately add flour and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and carefully fold into mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° to 325° for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
It should have a nice brown crust on top.

title: cottage delight
directions: Empty cottage cheese into bowl and sprinkle orange jello over it.
Add crushed pineapple, then mix in Dream Whip.
If too heavy, add up to 2 tablespoons of the pineapple juice.

title: green beans supreme
directions: Drain green beans.
Combine beans, soup and 1 can onions. Pour in casserole pan.
Put the other onion rings over all.
Bake 20 minutes in 400° oven.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: In pan, melt butter; add sugar and boil over low heat, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes.
Add milk; stir until milk comes to a boil.
Slowly add powdered sugar; beat with mixer until creamy or until thick enough to spread.
"Good on yellow cake."

title: coconut cream cheese frosting
directions: Melt 2 teaspoons butter in skillet; add coconut, stir constantly, over low heat until golden brown.
Spread coconut on paper towel to cool.
Cream butter and cheese; add milk, sugar and 1 3/4 cup coconut.
Spread on cake layers.
Sprinkle remainder on cake.

title: tartar punch
directions: Mix orange juice and sugar in a gallon of water; add acid. Set for 24 hours.
Not recommended for women who are pregnant.

title: cheesy nachos(microwave)
directions: Arrange tortilla chips on a 10-inch glass or paper plate. Place remaining ingredients in a plastic bag. Shake to mix. Sprinkle mixture over the chips. Microwave at 50% (Medium) for 3 to 8 minutes or until cheese melts, rotating plate 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Makes 24 nachos.

title: low calorie sweet and sour chicken
directions: Combine pineapple, salad dressing, onion and poppy seed.
Pour half of mixture in baking dish, place chicken on mixture and pour remaining mixture over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Serve over rice.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: rice pudding
directions: Bring to a boil and simmer 1 hour.
Take off stove.
Add 1 egg, beaten in 1 cup milk.
Add to rice and bring to a boil.
Add vanilla.

title: orange roughy parmesan
directions: In baking dish, place fillets in single layer.
Brush with lemon juice and let stand for 10 minutes.
In a small bowl, combine cheese, butter, mayonnaise, green onions, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Broil fillets 3 to 4 minutes under preheated broiler for 5 minutes.
Spread with cheese mixture and broil for an additional 2 to 3 minutes.
Watch closely!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix everything together.
Let simmer until onions are tender, about 30 to 45 minutes. Brush over chicken, ribs, chops, etc.

title: spinach pie
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Thaw spinach. Squeeze dry.
Beat cream cheese and half and half gradually.
Stir in Parmesan cheese, eggs, spinach, wheat germ and spices.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter and add to mixture.
Pour into shell and bake at 375° to 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can be kept refrigerated for 24 hours until ready to bake.

title: lemon-lime turkey, grilled
directions: Rinse the turkey and pat dry with paper towels.
Place in a large self-closing plastic bag.
In small bowl, stir together the soda, oil, soy sauce, horseradish and garlic powder.
Pour mixture over turkey in bag.
Seal bag and marinate the turkey in refrigerator for 2 hours, turning bag occasionally.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Add butter and let melt. Add other ingredients.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour or until brown.

title: easy sherbet punch
directions: In a large bowl, add ginger ale and sherbet ice cream. Serve chilled.

title: rhubarb jello jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar together and set aside for several hours to form juice. Boil 10 minutes stirring constantly. Cool a few minutes. Add jello. Stir well and refrigerate.

title: crock salad
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and celery seed.
Refrigerate. Cut peppers into small pieces.
Slice cucumbers, squash and zucchini in thin slices.
Pull cauliflowerets off in bite size pieces.
Pull flowerets from broccoli.
Mix all vegetables. Marinate overnight in the vinegar mixture.
Cook pasta according to directions on the package. Drain and cool.
Mix in with veggies and serve.

title: stuffed cucumbers
directions: Peel cucumbers.
Cut in half across the cucumber.
Scoop out inside and salt cavity.
Mix remaining ingredients and tightly stuff into the cucumbers.
Wrap with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Slice when ready to serve.

title: venison cheese balls
directions: Mix together ingredients, refrigerate 8 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: aunt mary's rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in warm water. Mix together warm milk, melted butter or shortening, sugar and salt. Add dissolved yeast and flour. Continue mixing for 5 minutes. Cover and let rise until double in bulk. Roll out into balls and let rise again for 1 1/2 hours (dough should be kept warm from mixing until baking). Bake 25 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cherry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cream butter and sugar with electric mixer in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add one egg; beat well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour and salt until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture by spooning lightly into measuring cup; set aside.
Press remaining crust mixture into prepared pan.
Bake 15 minutes. Blend remaining 2 to 4 tablespoons flour into reserved crust mixture until crumbly; set aside.

title: corn bread salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 12 servings.

title: fritz and magnum's homemade dog bone biscuits
directions: Combine by hand or in food processor the flour, wheat germ, cornmeal, sugar and bouillon. Add shortening and combine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal. Add egg and water and mix until mixture forms a ball.
Knead dough until smooth and elastic. Roll out onto floured board to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut out with cookie cutter and place on a circle of cardboard.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on Medium-high (70%).
Turn cookie over and microwave 2 to 3 minutes more.
Biscuits should be firm and dry to touch.
Cool on a wire rack. As they cool, they become crisp.
Man's best friend just loves these.

title: beefy round steak
directions: Place steak in 9 x 13-inch pan, lined with aluminum foil.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with soup mix and then spoon dot steak with cream of celery soup.
Bake at 400°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes until steak is tender.

title: carol paterson's original surprise chocolate cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Form mixture into balls the size of a large walnuts, "concealing" the walnuts and raisins inside each.
Roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press a piece of walnut on each, flattening slightly. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from tray and cool. Yields approximately 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread 1/2 can of undiluted soup in bottom of 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Place chicken breasts in casserole.
On top of each breast, place 1 slice of Swiss cheese.
Cover with remaining soup.

title: "ms. donna's" quick microwave fudge
directions: In a large (4-quart) microwave-safe bowl melt margarine.
Add 3 cups sugar and evaporated milk.
Mix well.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Mix well.
Scrape bowl and microwave for an additional
5 1/2 minutes, stirring after 3 minutes.
Remove from microwave.
Add morsels and stir until melted.
Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Store at room temperature. Makes 3 pounds.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream to serve. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Soften cream cheese and add undrained crushed pineapple.
Add pudding, then all Cool Whip and drained chunk pineapple. Refrigerate.

title: favorite three bean salad
directions: Combine beans and other ingredients.
Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: beef-egg scramble
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain any grease in pan.
Blend eggs and water; pour over meat mixture and scramble until eggs are set.
Lift cooked portions with spatula and turn to cook eggs evenly.
Serve in buns.

title: pork and sauerkraut
directions: *Use sauerkraut from a barrel or in packages from the dairy department, not canned.

title: tuna casserole
directions: "Butter a casserole very well.
Crackle up potato chips; I can't give portions, for I just use what I need.
Add one can of tuna, broken into bits.
Add one can of mushroom soup, and I also add enough canned milk, to make it quite wet.
Grate cheese over top; season with very little salt and a little Tabasco sauce. Bake about a half hour, until nice and brown on top."

title: pork sausage enchiladas
directions: Finely crumble sausage; cook with onion in 10-inch skillet. Drain well.
Stir in 1/4 cup of picante sauce and cumin.

title: turkey meatballs in lemon sauce
directions: Combine egg, cereal, Worcestershire sauce and lemon peel.
Add turkey; mix well.
Shape into 8 balls using about 1/4 cup mixture for each ball.
In 10-inch skillet, brown balls on all sides in hot oil; drain off fat.
Add broth; cover and simmer 20 minutes. Use a slotted spoon to transfer balls to a serving dish, reserving juices in pan.
In bowl, combine yogurt, cornstarch and lemon juice; add to juices in skillet.
Cook and stir until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes more.
Add carrot and onion.
Serve sauce over meatballs.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken enchilada soup
directions: Melt margarine in large deep skillet.
Saute onion until tender.
Add flour to make paste.
Add tomato/chicken broth and regular chicken broth.
Stir until well blended, no lumps.	Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add enchilada sauce and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Stir well.	Add cheese and stir until melted and broth is smooth. Add deboned chicken.
Place in crock-pot and simmer on low to blend all flavors and to heat through.
Serve with corn chips or tortilla chips.
WONDERFUL!!!

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon well.
In small sauce pan, melt margarine, stir in flour.
Beat in milk a little at a time, stirring constantly and cook until thickened.
Add salmon, bread crumbs, lemon juice, salt, pepper and red pepper.
Form into patties.
Saute in melted butter until heated through.
Serve plain or on buns.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant, celery, onion, salt and pepper in a small amount of water.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: tangy spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in covered jar.
When ready to drink spoon 2 1/2 to 3 teaspoons in cup and pour hot boiling water in cup.
Place candy cinnamon stick in tea and stir.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 2 baked pie shells.
Chill. Store any remaining pie in refrigerator.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornmeal, and eggs well.
Add oleo, milk, and vanilla and mix well.
Pour into 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350 for 45 - 50 minutes.

title: microwave tomato relish
directions: In microwave-safe bowl, combine celery, onions, oil, garlic and red pepper.
Cook, covered, on High for 1 1/2 minutes. Arrange tomato wedges in dish.
Add onion mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cook, covered, on High 4 minutes or until tomatoes are tender and heated.
Rotate dish once after 2 minutes.
Add seasoning.

title: brunch cheese puff
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
Four hours before serving, alternate layers of bread and cheese in greased shallow casserole and pour melted butter over top.
Beat eggs well; add salt, milk, pepper and mustard.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 3 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake 30 minutes more.

title: jerry's cheese bread spread
directions: Start with enough whipped butter or margarine to equal the desired quantity of spread.
Add ingredients to taste.
Mix and refrigerate for several hours for best flavor.
Spread on bread (crusty is best) and broil until brown and bubbly.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with cocoa and food coloring added to creamed mixture.
Add salt and buttermilk with flour and vanilla.
Add vinegar and soda.
Blend.
Do not beat hard.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cook in two greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Split layers and frost with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Brown ground meat and onion until
wilted.
Add rest of ingredients.
Clean out center of peppers.
Stuff peppers and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: potato crab cakes
directions: Prepare potatoes according to package directions; drain and pat dry.
Place in large bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients except oil.
Stir until well blended.
Shape into 8 patties. Place on waxed paper lined tray.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours. In large skillet heat oil over medium heat.
Add patties; cook until browned on both sides, about 10 minutes.

title: super duper spinach
directions: Cook and drain 3 packages of chopped spinach.
Mix with 1 package onion soup mix and the sour cream.
Bake in buttered casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.
May be topped with canned onion rings at last minute.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips and margarine together.
Beat eggs and add to chocolate mixture.
Add other ingredients.
Beat well. Pour into 9 x 13 inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut in square.

title: yummy pecans
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add brown sugar and vanilla flavoring; mix well.
Add pecans.
Drop by spoonfuls, containing about 3 pecan halves, onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off; leave Yummies in oven until cool.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package. Pour 1/2 of cake batter into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°. While the cake is baking, melt caramels with milk and butter. Pour over cake after 20 minutes. Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Pour the rest of the cake batter over cake. Return to oven and bake 20 more minutes at 250° and 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add melted margarine.
Beat eggs and stir in onions, mayonnaise and soup.
Fold this into broccoli. Sprinkle cheese and Ritz crackers on top.
Cook for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: amy's k. balls
directions: Heat Karo and sugar.
When it starts to bubble, take off heat and add peanut butter and mix.
Pour over the cereal and mix. When cool, shape into balls and put on wax paper.

title: chicken and biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients in a baking dish.
Grate cheese over top. Put uncooked biscuits from edge to edge.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: chicken marsala
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper in large plastic Baggie.
Coat chicken cutlets and brown in 3 tablespoons oil.
Remove chicken from pan.
Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add Marsala wine, white wine and chicken.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice peaches (if apples, add cinnamon) in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut crust from bread; cut each slice in 4 pieces and place on fruit.
Mix melted butter, sugar, flour and egg.
Pour on bread slices.
Coat each slice well.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: green mountain gingersnaps*
directions: Cream shortening in bowl.
Add sugar, molasses and egg, mix thoroughly.
Sift remaining ingredients together, stir into creamed mixture.
Roll into small balls, place on greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated 375° oven for about 10 minutes or until done.

title: spencer's hamburger
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for half hour.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: banana cake
directions: In a bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add bananas, buttermilk, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed, until mixed well, then go to medium speed for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 x 1 1/2-inch or 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy marinade for steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to use.
Yields 1 3/4 cups.

title: german caramel cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of the batter in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cajun fried shrimp
directions: Beat eggs and milk. Coat shrimp with spices. Dip shrimp in egg and milk mixture. Bread shrimp with cornmeal and flour mixture. Heat oil when ready fry shrimp for about 3 to 5 minutes until golden brown.

title: sliced green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes 1/8 inch thick.
Dissolve lime in enough water to cover tomatoes.
Soak 24 hours.
Drain and soak in cold water for 4 hours.
Change water every hour.
Make a syrup of sugar and 3 pints vinegar and pour hot syrup over tomatoes.
Let stand overnight.

title: zucchini special
directions: Put sliced zucchini into a casserole with lid. Brown bacon and onion. Crumble bacon and add broth to zucchini. Pour tomato sauce over all. Sprinkle Cheddar and Parmesan on top. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: taco meat filling
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain well.
Add chopped onions, chopped bell pepper, black pepper, salt, garlic powder and cumin.
Cook about 2 minutes. Add canned tomatoes and cook for about 10 minutes or until juice is mostly gone.
Warm taco shells in a 300° oven.
Fill with taco meat filling and garnish with shredded lettuce and tomato.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in beaten eggs.
Mix flour and spices, then mix flour with fruit, nuts and raisins. Add to butter mixture and blend well.
(Dough will be stiff.) Store in refrigerator for 2 days.
Roll in small balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, condensed milk and powdered sugar in large pan or mixing bowl.
Gently toss cake into milk mixture to moisten cake pieces.
(Tossing with hands works best and is a lot more fun.)
Dump cake into punch bowl or any large bowl.
Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Drizzle over cake mixture.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix together.
Add 1 tablespoon water if mixture is extra dry. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chuckwagon round-up
directions: Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Mix dry ingredients.
Combine milk, egg and oil.
Then add to dry ingredients, stirring until well mixed.
Spread on bottom and sides of pan.
Then mix beans, cheese, onion powder and oregano.
Cut hot dogs in 1/2-inch slices (leave 2 hot dogs).
Mix with beans.
Spoon into middle of pie pan.
Then cut 2 remaining hot dogs in half, then lengthwise half. Place on top of bean mixture skin side up in a spoke fashion.

title: caramel icing
directions: Slowly melt 1 cup sugar in saucepan (or iron skillet). Mix 2 cups sugar and milk in another saucepan and boil until first is melted (10 to 15 minutes). Stir constantly. Mix all together. Cook slowly until it forms a soft ball. Remove from heat and add butter. Let cool 5 minutes. Add vanilla. Beat until smooth. Frost a cake made with Duncan Hines butter recipe cake mix.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Debone and cut into small pieces. Pour into an 8 x 11-inch baking pan.
Heat together soup and bouillon cubes that have been dissolved in the boiling water. Pour over chicken.
Pour can of Veg-All on top.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put on crust and refrigerate (can be done the night before).

title: jalapeno dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in glass dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese.
Cut cheese in thin slices and layer over chili.
Bake in oven at 350° until cheese bubbles.	Serve with tortilla chips (white are best).
(Double recipe if you want a large dish.)

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat 6 egg whites until stiff.
Add cream of tartar.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat until stiff.
Fold in saltine crackers (crumbled by hand) into mix.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Prepare 2 packages Dream Whip and spread on top; refrigerate.
When cool, spread cherry pie filling on top.

title: round-up casserole
directions: In ungreased 2-quart casserole, place layer of rice.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and pepper.
Pour in 1 can tomato sauce and hot water.
Add layers of onion and green pepper, then a layer of ground beef.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Top with layer of corn.
Add chili powder to last can of tomato sauce; pour over corn.
Top with bacon slices.
Cover; bake for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
This may be made in 2 dishes and freeze one for later use.

title: pat's coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil milk, sugar and 1/2 cup of coconut for 1 minute.
Punch holes all over cake and pour mixture over cake.
Cool.
Mix 1/2 cup coconut and Cool Whip; spread over top.
Sprinkle coconut over all.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add vinegar gradually.
Add butter and cook until it starts to thicken, stirring constantly.
Add beaten eggs slowly, then add milk.
Cook on low heat until it starts to boil.

title: ham and cheese bake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 8 x 4-inch loaf pan. Arrange bread, overlapping in pan.
Top with vegetables, ham, 2 tablespoons green onions and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Sprinkle with remaining onions and let stand five minutes.
Bake uncovered 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: double pistachio cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Blend; then beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.
Top with Pistachio Frosting.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a shallow dish.
Dip each breast in milk; roll in crumb mix.
Place chicken in lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 18 minutes or until done. Serves 6. A family favorite recipe!

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Let brown a little. Mix flour, sugar and milk until smooth, then pour into margarine. Spoon fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: all-bran brown bread
directions: Grease pan well.
Combine milk and vinegar.
Mix sugar, salt, bran and flour.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Let stand 1 hour before baking.
Pour into bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chewy-o's
directions: Heat pudding and corn syrup in large pan.
Let boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Stir until melted.
Add Cheerios and mix until completely covered with chocolate.
Put into 8 x 8-inch greased pan and let cool.
Cut into squares when ready to serve.

title: chinese christmas cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Mix next four until smooth.
Pour batter over floured fruit until all is coated.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: cheese toast
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour and cayenne pepper and cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.
Slowly add milk, stirring constantly until smooth and thickened.
Stir in cheese and cook until melted.
Add salt to taste.
Beat 2 tablespoons hot cheese mix into yolks.
Return the yolk-cheese mixture to the saucepan and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly for 1 to 2 minutes until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Gently fold in the egg whites and mound on toast.
They must be eaten as soon as they are prepared.

title: wiener roll-ups
directions: Cut wieners into 1-inch pieces, then roll up in strips of crescent rolls.
Bake on cookie sheet in 425° oven until golden brown.
Serve with slaw and potato salad.

title: ericka's pear salad
directions: Mash pears and cream cheese together.
Boil juice from pears and add Jell-O.
Add pears and cheese to Jell-O.
Let jell.
Fold in whipped cream, nuts and cherries.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix together.
Skin chicken breasts and lay in mixture.
Pour 1 package of Lipton onion soup mix on top of chicken breasts. Foil top.
Bake at 350° or 375° for 2 hours.

title: sour cream potatoes on grill
directions: Place potatoes in center of 14-inch square of heavy-duty foil. Spread with butter.
Blend remaining ingredients and pour over potatoes.
Close foil and fold into secure package.
Grill over flame at medium setting 20 to 30 minutes.
Turn occasionally.

title: beef casserole
directions: Cook meat, onion, celery and pepper in hot fat until onion is golden.
Season.
Add soy sauce and tomato soup.
Heat to boiling. Pour over noodles and mix.
Bake in a 2-quart size casserole for 350° for 30 minutes.

title: coconut bon-bons
directions: Cream the cream cheese until soft.
Add sugar gradually, blending well.
Add vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Form in small balls and roll in coconut.
Chill until firm.
Store covered in refrigerator.

title: harvest fruit bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine fruit, orange juice, bananas and 1 teaspoon apple spice in medium bowl.
Set aside, stirring occasionally.
In large bowl, beat together margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add combined flour, oats and 1/2 teaspoon apple spice; beat until crumbly.
Reserve 3/4 cup oat mix for topping. Press remaining oat mixture into 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: nada's kool-aid slush punch
directions: Mix all the above and freeze; thaw to a slush and add 1 bottle of ginger ale before serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook bacon and crisp it up.
Fix broccoli and put in bowl. Mix onion, bacon, sunflower seeds, mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Pour over broccoli and let set overnight.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a casserole dish. Heat in oven until bubbly.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix; pour into vanilla wafer crust.
Chill until set.
Makes 1 large pie or 2 small pies.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs, add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherry bars
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs and rest of ingredients, except pie mix.
Spread half in greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Spread cherry pie mix to cover.
Put rest of dough on top. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit dip
directions: In small bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve with fresh fruit, graham crackers or vanilla wafers.
Best if chilled overnight.

title: no bake chocolate balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in balls.
Dip in chocolate mixture with a toothpick.
Place on waxed paper.

title: creamy fresh corn
directions: Cut and scrape corn from cob (makes 3 cups).
Cook bacon slowly until crisp; remove and reserve.
Stir corn into hot bacon fat.
Add water, salt and sugar; stir and cook for 5 minutes, uncovered.
Stir flour into milk; mix until smooth.
Add to corn and stir constantly until thickened.
Add pepper and butter. Serve hot; garnish with reserved bacon.
Yields 6 servings.

title: favorite blueberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add water and 1 large cup blueberries. Cook over medium-high heat and stir until thick. Add butter and the rest of the blueberries. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with whipped cream.

title: chutney cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients in food processor until smooth.
Put in Saran Wrap lined bowl to mold.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Remove Saran Wrap and top with chutney and chives.

title: perfect vegetable dip
directions: Pour into center of a relish tray or a serving dish. Arrange vegetables (carrots, broccoli, cauliflower etc.) around dip. Perfectly delicious!

title: reese's cookie cups
directions: Place cupcake wrappers on cookie sheet.
Fill with cookie dough, usually 1/2 teaspoon. Bake according to package directions.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour in a greased pie pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate walnut drops
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients over medium heat.
Add milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop from a teaspoon onto wax paper.
Makes 32 pieces.

title: mexi-chili dip
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a small bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to vegetable mixture.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serve with corn chips.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: hearty dip for chips
directions: Fry ground chuck, sausage and onions.
Drain grease.
Pour mixture into crock-pot.
Mix together soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes. Then add to crock-pot.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add to mixture (mix well).
When cheese is melted, dip is ready to serve with your favorite chips.

title: molasses butterball cookies
directions: In mixer bowl, beat butter on medium speed of electric mixer for 30 seconds.
Add molasses and beat until fluffy.
Add flour to butter mixture.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Stir in nuts.

title: vegetable powder
directions: With blender or food processor, pulverize all ingredients. Store in covered jar.
Use to enrich soups, stews, meats, salad dressings and cooked vegetables.

title: nuts and bolts(party mix)
directions: I cut the measurement on all the sauces and salts by 1/4 teaspoon.
Using the recipe amounts makes it more spicy.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Mix together and spread into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
When done, take out of oven and spread 1 (6 ounce) package semi-sweet chocolate morsels on top.
Put in the oven, but turn it off.
Heat until they look waxy.

title: swiss treats
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir into creamed mixture.
Add nuts, cherries, coconut and chocolate chips.
Spread dough in greased jelly roll pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly and cut into bars.
Makes about seven dozen.

title: baked-tomato spaghetti
directions: Cut tomatoes lengthwise and place, cut side up, in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix garlic, 1/3 cup parsley and 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Pat mixture over cut side of tomatoes.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons oil over tomatoes.
Bake at 425° until browned on top, 60 to 70 minutes.

title: fish stir-fry
directions: In large skillet, combine oil and butter. Add bell pepper, onion, garlic, crushed red pepper, fish and lemon juice.
Cook on medium to low heat until fish is tender.
Then add soy sauce. Serves 6.

title: thirty day cake
directions: Combine Starter, 2 cups sugar and peaches and juice.
Stir every day for 10 days.
On the 10th day, add 2 cups sugar and pineapple and juice.
Stir every day for 10 days.
On the 20th day, add 2 cups sugar, fruit cocktail and juice and cherries.
Stir every day for 10 days.
On the 30th day, drain juice from fruit and divide fruit into thirds.
Makes 3 cakes.
You will have enough juice for 4 to 5 starters.

title: festive cauliflower casserole
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Cook, covered, in a small amount of boiling water, 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain; set aside.

title: gold fingers
directions: Boil chicken until fork tender.
Cool.
Then remove skin and break meat into 2-inch pieces.
In a mixing bowl, mix egg and then add milk, flour, baking powder and salt.
Heat oil in frying pan. Dip chicken fingers in batter; then saute until brown, turning once.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat for 4 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cold taco dip
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients, then add sour cream last.
After mixed, spread on a dinner plate.
Cover with cling wrap and refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: baileys shiny top cobbler
directions: Spread fruit in well-greased cake pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine flour, 1 1/2 cups sugar, milk, butter, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt (batter will be thick).
Spoon over berries and spread to edges of baking dish; set aside.
In small bowl, mix remaining 1 1/2 cups sugar, cornstarch and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Sprinkle over batter.
Pour boiling water over all.
Bake in 350° oven 1 hour until golden brown and glazed.

title: chicotsky's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain well in colander.
Stir a few times after draining.
After cooling in colander for about 5 minutes, add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Add cheese and mix lightly.
Add salad dressing, the amount used will depend on your taste and the amount of liquid the pasta absorbed when cooking.
Chill until served.
Pasta salad will keep well in the refrigerator.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Combine oil, sea salt, garlic and paprika.
Brush chicken pieces with mixture, then roll in wheat germ.
Place, skin side down, in a shallow baking pan and brush each piece again with the oil mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Turn each piece and bake until brown and tender.

title: cherry caramel ring
directions: Place butter in 8-inch round dish and microwave until melted, 1/2 to 3/4 minute.
Sprinkle sugar over butter and add corn syrup. Stir well with fork.
Place drinking glass in center of dish. Sprinkle with pecans and cherries.
Arrange biscuits over mixture in dish in petal shape, squeezing to fit, if necessary.
Microwave at Medium 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes. Remove glass and invert onto serving plate.
Let dish stand over rolls a few minutes so remaining syrup in dish may drizzle over rolls.
Serve warm.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Peel potatoes, and slice.
Cook until done.
Combine sour cream, soup, salt and pepper.
Layer potatoes, ham and sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and let it sit overnight.
Serve with crackers or chips of your choice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs until smooth.
Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Fold in fruit cocktail.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: time-to-spare-ribs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Shake flour in large size (14 x 20-inch) cooking bag.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Roll down top of bag.
Add barbecue sauce, onion and green pepper.
Squeeze bag gently to blend ingredients.
Cut ribs in serving size pieces; place in bag.
Turn bag gently to coat the ribs with sauce. Arrange ribs in an even layer.
Close bag with nylon tie; make six 1/2-inch slits on top.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes; cook with skins on in boiling salt water to cover until tender.
Let cool slightly; peel and slice warm potatoes into pot or large mixing bowl.
Add onions and celery seed.
Set aside.
Fry bacon in large skillet.
When browned, remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper toweling.
Leave enough fat in skillet to cover bottom of pan.
Keep warm.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: In medium saucepan, combine broccoli and water.
Simmer, covered, for about 10 minutes.
Drain and reserve liquid, adding water if necessary to make 1 cup.
In small saucepan, melt margarine.
Blend in flour to form a smooth paste.
Slowly add the cup of reserved liquid.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Season as desired. Combine sauce with broccoli and rice.
Serve as a side dish. Yields 4 servings.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Blend well. Store in the refrigerator.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute onion, garlic and green pepper, then add meat (cook if not already cooked).
Add steamed rice and add 1/2 cup soy sauce. Mix ingredients.
Add cubed scrambled eggs.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until tender.
Mix the soup and milk together before adding to cooked potatoes.
Add the spices.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not boil.
Serve piping hot.

title: fruit crush punch
directions: Mix water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit juices.
Pour into ice cube trays and freeze.
When ready, put in bowl and pour in Sprite.
Mix until slushy.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and shape into a ball.

title: sugar cream bars
directions: Beat ingredients together with mixer and spread on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (or until golden brown).
Let cool before cutting.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix yeast and warm water.
Blend in the remaining ingredients. Let rise until double.
Dissolve into 3 parts.
Roll each into a circle and cut into 12 pieces as for pie.
Roll starting at wide end.
Let rise again until double.
Bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook all ingredients together, except chicken.
Add chicken. Pour into dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: baked omelet
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Put 6 slices of bread in bottom.
Top slice of bread with a slice of cheese, ham and another slice of bread.
Mix eggs, milk and mustard (blender) and pour over sandwiches in pan.
Refrigerate overnight and 1/2 hour before baking, sprinkle with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut krispy treats
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and peanut butter in large glass bowl.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes or until sugar is melted, stirring only once.
Stir in vanilla.
Fold in cereal and peanuts. Spread into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cover and chill one hour or until set.
Cut into small squares.
Good lunchbox treat.

title: ham and cheese breakfast casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients; mix.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: marbled brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare Cream Cheese Filling.
Heat butter and chocolate over low heat, stirring occasionally, until melted. Cool.
Beat chocolate mixture, sugar, vanilla and eggs in a 2 1/2-quart bowl on medium speed for 1 minute.
Beat in flour and salt on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Spread half the batter in greased square pan (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Spread with Cream Cheese Filling.
Gently spread remaining batter over Cream Cheese Filling.
Swirl through batter with spoon in an over-and-under motion for marbled effect.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (55 to 65 minutes).
Cool; cut into bars. Makes about 46 to 48 bars.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water, stir in cheese until melted.
Add crushed pineapple, chill.
Add 1 cup pecans, cut into pieces.
Add 1 pkg. Dream Whip (use both envelopes).
Stir, then chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: umbaday ky bhajy
directions: Cook spinach, chilis, ginger-garlic, salt together.
Let set for 15 minutes and then puree.
Add water while cooking.

title: skillet cornbread
directions: Cast-iron skillet is needed.

title: betty's shrimp stew
directions: Saute onion and bell peppers in olive oil. Add all other ingredients along with shrimp and cook until tender.

title: asparagus loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into buttered casserole or loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Place in greased 10-inch pie plate.
(No pie crust needed.)
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet peas
directions: Open can and pour into a saucepan.
Heat on medium and add margarine and pepper.
Cook approximately 15 to 20 minutes or until well heated.
Um-um good!

title: chocolate layer cookies
directions: Melt unsweetened chocolate with 1/2 cup margarine; let cool. Beat egg and sugar until thick.
Add almonds and flour. Stir until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool.

title: deviled swiss steak
directions: In a large skillet, saute onion and garlic in shortening until lightly brown.
Cut steak into strips and dredge in flour.
Brown well in pan with onions and garlic.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Simmer on low heat until meat is tender (covered), approximately 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: root beer cookies
directions: Beat together and spread on cooled cookies.

title: pecan baked chicken
directions: Whisk buttermilk, eggs, lemon juice, 2 teaspoon salt, 1 1/2 teaspoon red pepper, and garlic in a large bowl.
Add chicken. Cover and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes or overnight.
Heat oven to 400°.
Process bread crumbs and pecans in food processor until nuts are finely ground.
Transfer to large bowl; stir in remaining 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2 teaspoon red pepper, and black pepper.
Remove chicken from marinade with tongs, letting excess marinade drip off.	Roll chicken in crumb mixture to coat. Arrange in single layer on 9
x 13	x 2
inch pan. Drizzle with butter. Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until instant read meat thermometer registers 170°. Transfer chicken to paper towels to drain.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: peach dessert
directions: Melt butter and combine other ingredients, except peaches. Put in a 1 1/2 or 2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Add partially drained peaches on top, arranging evenly.
Bake at 350° until bottom rises and gets brown.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Layer in casserole.
Repeat layers and top with grated cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: matrimony cake(date cookie)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and rub in butter until crumbly.

title: chipped beef and cheese
directions: Combine first four ingredients and mix well.
Spread mixture on slices of chipped beef.
Roll up and cut each roll in half. Garnish top of each with a sprig of fresh parsley.
Chill.

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Refrigerate until partially set.
Whip and mix in 1/2 cup chopped celery, nut meats, crushed pineapple, cream cheese (mashed with a fork for easy mixing) and whipping cream.
Pour into mold and garnish with cherries.

title: seven layer cookie
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread graham cracker crumbs on top.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients in order.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling, pineapple and pecans in two quart baking dish and stir.
Spread dry cake mix evenly over mixture.
Place pats of margarine over dry cake mix.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until brown.

title: peach glaze
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients together in a saucepan.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add the next 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick.
Add the jello.
Mix well.
Cool.
Add the peaches and pour into the pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: beignets(makes 36)
directions: Place water in bowl.
Sprinkle with yeast.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, salt, milk, egg and shortening in large bowl.
Stir in yeast and gradually add flour.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate several hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix sour cream and soups together and pour over chicken. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle mushrooms on top.
Prepare Stove Top stuffing mix according to directions and then add on top of chicken.
Cover with foil loosely.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package, except use juice from oranges instead of water.
Then add oranges and nuts.

title: sir jax triangle tip roast
directions: Preheat oven to 500° and cook for 15 minutes.
Turn oven down to 350° and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not cover.
Do not turn. Cook with fat side up.

title: hot tuna fish sandwiches
directions: Make tuna salad as usual.
Drain one small can of pineapple tidbits.
Cut each tidbit in two pieces and mix with tuna salad. Add cheese (shredded or cubed).
Spread mixture on hamburger buns. Wrap each bun individually in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: banana split ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except milk.
Pour in churn and add enough milk to bring mixture to fill-line.
Stir.
Continue to churn ice cream according to the directions for your churn.

title: oysters casino
directions: Fry bacon until partially cooked.
Add onion and celery. Cook until tender.
Add lemon juice and seasoning. Arrange oysters in well-greased shallow baking dish.
Spread bacon mixture over oysters.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until edges of oysters begin to curl. Serve as appetizers or over toast points.

title: tropical punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients in a 2 gallon container.
Add enough water to make 2 gallons.
Chill and garnish with lemon or orange slices.

title: chicken with almonds
directions: Put chicken in a baking dish.
Mix all the ingredients listed, except the almonds.
Pour the mixture over the chicken.
Sprinkle with the paprika and almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: apple-walnut cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and 1/2 cup of nuts.
Place apples in bottom of a greased 8 1/4 x 1 3/4-inch round baking dish. Sprinkle sugar mixture on top.

title: caramel rolls
directions: Thaw bread but don't allow to rise.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Tear one loaf into pieces and drop helter skelter into pan.
Melt butter; add rest of ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour over the torn loaf.
Tear second loaf and throw on top, trying to fill in spaces.
Let rise 2 1/2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Raisins can be added before baking.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt and pepper. Stir in milk until smooth.
Add mustard and margarine.
Stirring constantly, bring to a boil over medium-high heat and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add macaroni.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with croutons.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 6.

title: hot onion souffle
directions: Thaw frozen onions.
Roll in paper towels to squeeze out excess moisture.

title: good and easy pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Knead for 1 to 2 minutes.
Roll out and put in well-greased pizza pans.
Top with favorite toppings. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cambrisson salad
directions: Combine beef, eggs, tomatoes and anchovies.
Serve on lettuce with dressing.
Serves 6.

title: fresh crab saucegarlic crabs
directions: Option:
After cooking crabs in oil, garlic, hot pepper and parsley,
continue
to
cook until crabs are done about 10 more minutes.
Serve like this for a great tasting crab.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix in blender.
Store in jar in refrigerator.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: chicken and yellow rice
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients until chicken is done; drain off broth and save. Cook yellow rice as per directions on package using some of the chicken broth for the liquid (save about 1/2 to 1 quart of broth to use later). Add soy sauce. When cooking rice, combine in a large mixing bowl, deboned chicken (cooked), cooked rice, mushroom and celery soups, chili powder and sour cream. Add chicken broth until mixture is soupy. Pour into greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Layer bananas on crust.
Combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Pour over bananas.
Next, add pineapple and then top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with coconut, cherries and pecans.
Chill and serve.

title: veal, italian style
directions: Remove and discard any excess fat from cutlets.
Place cutlets on waxed paper, and flatten to 1/8 inch thickness with a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; stir well. Combine egg and milk, beating well.
Combine breadcrumbs and paprika, stirring well.
Dredge cutlets in flour mixture; then dip in egg mixture, and thorougly coat with beadcrumb mixture.
Pour oil into a 12x8x2 inch baking dish; arrange cutlets in dish. Cover with waxed paper and microwave at Medium (50% power) for 14 to 16 minutes or until done.
Spoon Italian tomato sauce over cutlets; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese, and top with Parmesan. Microwave, uncovered, at High for 3 to 4 minutes or until sauce thickens.
Yield about 1 cup.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar and then add the egg.
Mix well. Mix flour, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg together; add to creamed mixture and blend until smooth.
Add mashed banana and oatmeal next.
Blend.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased sheet and bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni with onion.
Drain and place in casserole dish. Melt Velveeta cheese with tomatoes and water.
Pour over macaroni. Bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: pound cake
directions: Have cream cheese and butter at room temperature.
Mix cream cheese and butter.
Add the sugar, eggs, and slowly add the flour. Follow with the vanilla and lemon extract.
Preheat oven to 325°. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes (approximate).

title: pancit(a philippine recipe)
directions: Dip pork in flour; brown in small amount of oil.
Add salt, pepper and water.
Cook until tender.
Add soy sauce, vinegar, green beans, carrot and cabbage.
Cook for 5 minutes, adding more water if needed.
Add the noodles; stir constantly until heated through.
Serve, garnished with kalamansi or lemon wedges to be squeezed on top, if desired.

title: beefy beans
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: creamy custard sauce
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix and cinnamon.
Beat until well blended.
Cover.
Refrigerate until ready to serve. Serve with fresh fruit.

title: quick tapioca pudding
directions: Mix tapioca, sugar, salt, egg and milk in saucepan.
Let stand 5 minutes, then bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Stir once after 20 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: homemade brownies
directions: Melt Choco Bake and butter until melted (2 minutes).
Mix in sugar and eggs. Stir in flour and vanilla. Add nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
When done, toothpick should come out clean.

title: unusual kind o' cracker spread
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° until top is crusty and brown. Serve with Melba toast or rye crackers.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Note:
The last four ingredients, use to taste, more or less.

title: frosting mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add to Seven Minute Frosting. Spread over Cherry Pineapple Cake layers (see recipe for Cherry Pineapple Cake).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing per package directions.
Stir in margarine. Place 1/2 on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Boil zucchini with onion. Drain well.
Add soup, sour cream and carrot.
Place zucchini mixture on top of stuffing.
Top with remaining stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: no bake banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
Add Eagle Brand milk.
Beat with mixer.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold in vanilla, layer bananas, wafers and pudding.

title: empress meat loaf
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until onion is transparent; stir in thyme.
Toss into bread crumbs and parsley. Lightly mix together ground beef and remaining ingredients.
Pack half of meat mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread stuffing over meat, then remainder of meat.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: mini reubens
directions: Spread mustard on party rye.
Place one slice of corned beef, a little sauerkraut and a slice of cheese on each piece of bread. Leave open-faced.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower and green onions in bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and sugar.
Pour over cauliflower and green onions. Add Parmesan cheese and salt and pepper.
Let set overnight. Before serving, add lettuce and bacon and toss.

title: fried spinach
directions: Fry bacon.
Once bacon is cooked, remove from pan and place on a paper towel.
Drain half of grease and place it on the side.
In the remaining grease, in the pan, place spinach and onion.
Let cook.
If it begins to dry add a couple of teaspoons of water. Once the spinach has cooked, stir in the bacon (crumbled).
Serve hot.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Blend the shortening, brown sugar and granulated sugar.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients together in a separate bowl.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Stir in 1 cup M&M's. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Decorate with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hot cocoa
directions: Use recipe for Hot Cocoa.
Make the cocoa syrup and cool it. Add rest of water, milk and vanilla.
Stir or beat until smooth. Chill quickly.
Stir before serving.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir in soups and milk; heat thoroughly.
Garnish, if desired, with shredded Cheddar cheese, diced, cooked ham or bacon.

title: baked custard
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; pour into 2 cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of hot water in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Mix orange tidbits, marshmallows, sour cream, pineapple and coconut and chill overnight.

title: classic macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain and keep hot.
Toss 12 ounces cheese with the flour, onion, mustard, salt and pepper.
Combine with hot macaroni; pour in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Pour milk over macaroni.
Top with remaining cheese and dot with butter.
Bake at 375° or 350° for 45 minutes until macaroni is firm and golden brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook ground beef and seasonings.
Drain on paper towel. Spread meat on bottom of glass pan.
Add cheese, mashed potatoes, then more cheese over potatoes.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine vinegar, oil, parsley, salt, pepper, sugar and lemon juice in crock and cover.
Add garlic and mushrooms; cover and marinate overnight.

title: chicken quiche
directions: Saute the first 3 ingredients.
Mix milk, eggs, cornstarch, salt, pimento, and chicken with saute mix.
Pour in pie shell. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Shake paprika over top.
Bake 400° for 10 minutes.
Then 350° for 25 minutes or until set.

title: beans creole casserole
directions: To prepare lima beans, soak washed beans in warm water for 1 hour and rinse.
Cover with salted water and cook until tender (about 1 hour).
Be careful liquid does not cook down too low. Drain beans, but save some of the water.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix all ingredients, then pour in melted butter.
Mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Add the rest of the ingredients. Mix well. Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put pie filling in pan and cover with the dry cake mix.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Can be served with whipped cream or ice cream.
A rather rich cake.

title: scalloped tomatoes #1
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole with croutons.
Top with some of the tomatoes and sauce.
Continue the three layers, ending with croutons.
Top with Parmesan.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: japanese odango
directions: Put mochiko and tofu into a mixing bowl.
Knead them very well.
Form into small round balls.
Boil a lot of water in a large pot.
Put small balls into boiled water.
Take out small balls when they float on water.
Mix the balls and Azuki-an (sweat beans).

title: grilled cheese sandwiches
directions: Butter 1 side of each slice of bread, on the unbuttered side, place a slice of cheese, placing the other slice of bread on top of cheese, buttered side up.
In a medium low skillet, cook each side of the sandwich about 2 minutes, turning until lightly browned and cheese is melted in center.
You can add a slice of ham before cooking to make a grilled ham and cheese sandwich.

title: appetizer meatballs in sauce(served in your choice of sauce)
directions: Preheat oven to 500 degrees.

title: pizza bread
directions: Note:
Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Butter sides and bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix well first five ingredients.
Put chicken pieces on top with dry onion soup mix.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek.

title: frank and noodle cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Drain.
Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Combine soup, cream, tomato sauce, 1 cup cheese and oregano.
Add onion and pepper.
Add noodles and franks.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: warm rice salad
directions: Put olive oil in deep nonstick pan.
Add cooked rice and egg. Cook until egg is done and rice is hot.
Add soy sauce.
Dice up tomato, onions and cucumber.
Add the hot rice to them.
You can add more soy sauce to it if you like.
Serve warm.
(Very good.)

title: sparkies candy
directions: Crisp puffed wheat in oven at 350° for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cook corn syrup, sugar and water until it reaches soft ball stage.
Add butter and cook to hard brittle stage.
Add salt and puffed wheat. Stir until all are well coated.
Turn out into shallow greased pan or form into balls.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix 1 cup of pineapple juice (add water if less than 1 cup) and vanilla pudding.
Cook until thick, then cool slightly.
Pour over pineapple chunks and drained mandarin oranges.
Add sliced bananas before serving.
Decorate with maraschino cherries if desired.

title: lo-cal dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water until tender, drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese; heat and stir until melted.
remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.
Transfer to an ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
In a small skillet, melt remaining oleo.
Cook and stir crumbs in oleo until lightly browned; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: japanese rice
directions: Cook rice for 10 minutes; drain well.
While rice drains, fry (scramble) the egg.
Butter skillet; pour rice into skillet, along with fried egg.
Add mushrooms, peas, soy sauce and mustard sauce, along with butter.
Turn heat to medium-high; stir well.
When mixture begins to fry, turn heat to medium.
Continue to stir for about 5 minutes, or until well cooked.
Salt and pepper to taste. (To cut down on sodium, use lite soy sauce.)

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Skin chicken.
Remove fat.
Season with small amount of salt, pepper and paprika.
Saute minced garlic 1 minute in small amount of oil.
Rapidly brown chicken.
Place rice in greased casserole, water and chicken.
Pour soups over all.
Cook, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and cook 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: spinach squares
directions: Mix all together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
May be baked ahead and reheated.

title: strawberry romance
directions: Completely dissolve strawberry jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 packages of frozen strawberries.
Break up and stir until completely defrosted.
Add can of pineapple and chopped nuts. Pour half of the mixture into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or ring mold.
Jell.
Spread one small container of sour cream over set mixture, then add remaining mixture on top.
Let set.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: breakfast before
directions: Spray or grease a large rectangular Pyrex baking dish.
Break trimmed bread coarsely and line dish.
Brown sausage and drain. Layer sausage on top of bread.
Layer cheese on top of sausage. Beat eggs with a fork; mix with milk and mustard.
Pour over top of casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll in crushed nuts or paprika.

title: denver mint peas
directions: In saucepan, cook peas until hot; drain.
Stir butter, jelly and oregano into hot peas until butter and jelly are melted. Serve immediately.

title: old fashioned apple nut bars
directions: Mix well the sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add apples and walnuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham strada
directions: Cube bread.
Place on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add cheese, broccoli and ham.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over ham mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 55 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: "5" layered chicken divan
directions: *I have used frozen rice/broccoli/cheese in a pouch as an excellent substitute.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Put apples in the bottom of pan.
Pour 1/3 cup sugar and 1 cup orange juice over apples.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour and margarine or butter until real coarse.
Put on top of apples. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: chicken salad balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Shape into small balls and roll in cracker crumbs.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Dice the bread.
Put in greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over.
Sprinkle meat over cheese.
Beat eggs with 2 1/4 c. milk, and pour over meat.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Sift flour and cocoa together and set aside. Cream margarine and Crisco. Add sugar and cream well. Add eggs, one at a time. Add milk and flour alternately. Add extracts and food coloring. Mix thoroughly on medium speed of electric mixer and pour into greased tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: macaroni saute
directions: Saute macaroni, onion, green pepper and garlic in hot oil until macaroni turns slightly yellow.
Add tomato juice and the seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and boil for about 1 minute. Keep covered and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Combine the olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a shallow dish. Place the cornflakes in a separate shallow dish. Roll the chicken strips in the lemon mixture, then the cornflakes. Place on baking sheet. Pour any excess lemon mixture or cornflakes over the chicken strips. Bake for 15 minutes or until cooked through.

title: mound cake
directions: Mix cake mix and 1 stick margarine.
Bake on a cookie sheet or pie pan (the thinner the cake baked, the better).
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple bread
directions: Measure 3 cups of presifted flour and sift with cinnamon, salt, baking powder and soda.
Set aside.
In large bowl, mix together eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and apples.
Add flour mixture. Add nuts.
Mix.
Divide into 2 greased 8 x 4-inch bread pans. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: garden pasta salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, parsley, basil and garlic.
Mix well. Add cheese, broccoli and cooked and drained noodles.
Mix.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. While still
hot,
spread
1 large jar marshmallow cream over cake and cool.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Bring tomato soup, vinegar, sugar, oil and Worcestershire sauce to a boil.
Arrange sliced carrots in a shallow baking dish.
Pour mixture over carrots.
Top with bell pepper and onion rings. Simmer in 350° oven until onions and bell peppers are tender.
May be served warm or chilled.

title: french dressing
directions: Beat well. Optional:
Add 1 wedge crumbled Roquefort cheese.

title: brownie trifle
directions: Mix pudding mixes with milk.
Layer 1/2 of the brownies broken up in trifle bowl.
Layer 1/2 pudding, then Cool Whip.
Repeat. Sprinkle crumbled candy bars on top.
Chill.

title: mashed potato cakes
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
In a bowl, lightly beat one egg.
Add the onion, potatoes, flour, salt and pepper.
Shape into patties (4 to 6).
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Lightly beat remaining egg; stir in water.
Brush over potato cakes.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Eat topped with gravy.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and hash browns.
Place crescent rolls in a 12-inch pizza pan with points facing center to form crust.
Spoon sausage and hash browns.
Top with cheese.
Beat eggs, salt and milk.
Pour over crust. Sprinkle Parmesan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 or 8.

title: 100 good cookies
directions: Mix butter, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add cooking oil, egg and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Stir in coconut, oatmeal, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: easy apple dessert
directions: Cut the apples in half, core, slice thinly and don't peel apples.
Drop slices into a bowl of cold water.
Set aside. Combine flour, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Mix well. Beat the egg in a medium bowl.
Stir in brown sugar, honey and vanilla.
Blend in well drained apples and the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Fold in walnuts and raisins.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot, topped with French vanilla ice cream.
Makes one 9-inch pie plate, 4 servings.

title: oven fried chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken in egg and milk.
Dredge in flour mixture and seasonings.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Pour margarine over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Mix hash brown potatoes and onions and place in a 10 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Mix together sour cream and chicken soup; spread over the potato and onion mixture.
Top with melted margarine.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Top lightly with crumbled cornflakes.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, stir together, flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, melted shortening and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread evenly in buttered 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa over batter.
Pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
To serve, cut into squares and use spatula to invert each square onto a dessert plate, then spoon sauce from baking pan over the top.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and beat until fluffy.
Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, nutmeg and salt. Blend into creamed mixture to make a stiff cookie dough.
Shape into balls the size of walnuts.
Mix the 2 tablespoons sugar with the 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a small bowl.
Roll cookie balls in the cinnamon sugar.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until very lightly browned.

title: easter fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill 24 hours.
Serves 12.

title: mandel brot
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Split pumpkin and clean out seeds.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until flesh is tender.
Scoop out and puree in blender.
Cool. Add eggs, milk, sugar, corn syrup, salt and spices to pumpkin. Beat until smooth.
Pour into shells and bake at 350° until set 35 to 40 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: steak sandwiches(microwave)
directions: Microwave peppers and onions in margarine on High for 3 minutes in covered 1 1/2
quart bowl.
Add meat;
microwave on High for 2 minutes,
stirring after 1 minute.
Microwave Cheez Whiz until smooth consistency.
On
one
side of rolls, spread meat mixture.
Microwave on
High
for
seconds and spread with Cheez Whiz.
Yield:
6 sandwiches.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix together yellow cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter until smooth and press in bottom of a 9 x 13 buttered pan.

title: layered dessert
directions: Mix flour,
butter
and
nuts as you would a pie crust. Press into a
greased
x
13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Let cool completely.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and broccoli in margarine;
mix with other ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Bake
at
350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for 9 minutes.
Water should cover macaroni.
Do not drain off all water.
Leave a little.
Place alternate layers of macaroni and cheese in casserole dish.
Beat eggs and milk well.
Pour over macaroni and cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Should be moist inside and golden brown outside.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: blackie's chili
directions: Brown meat seasoned with garlic powder, salt and comino.
Add water and cook slowly for approximately 1 or 1 1/2 hours, or until meat is done.
Add chili powder and paprika.
Stir.
Then add chili beans or red kidney beans (drain juice).
Let simmer for a few minutes to blend in flavor.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion with flour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes. Add beans and simmer a few minutes longer. If too thick, add tomato juice.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add oil, cold water, eggs and pumpkin.
Bake at 325°
for 50 to 60 minutes or until pulls away from sides of pan.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: before and after barbecue chicken
directions: Boil chicken for approximately 10 minutes before church (approximately 9:30 a.m.).
Place chicken in casserole dish and pour barbecue sauce over chicken.
Place in oven at 300°.
After church (approximately 12:30 p.m.), chicken will be done and all you'll have to do is cook the pastry or noodles.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and
put
in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°, then for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna dill sandwich
directions: Stir together dressing, dill and pepper.
Add tuna, onions and carrots; mix together thoroughly.
For each sandwich, top one muffin half with lettuce, cheese slice and tuna mixture.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add broccoli to boiling water.
After thawed, cook an additional 5 minutes; drain thoroughly.
Mix all other ingredients, except crackers.
Add drained broccoli and stir. Crumble crackers on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until set.

title: cocktail hot dogs
directions: Melt jelly and mustard together over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Boil hot dogs, cut in pieces, in water for a minute or two.
Drain and add them to the jelly mixture.
Slowly let mixture come to a boil.
Cool and refrigerate until time to serve. They are better if you make them a couple of days ahead.
Heat again and keep warm in a fondue pot or chafing dish.
A crock pot works well too.

title: baked lasagna casserole
directions: Brown beef in oil with onion, garlic and parsley.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper; simmer for 1 hour.
Cook lasagna in water until soft.
Mix eggs and Ricotta cheese.
In an oblong pan, spread 1/2 cup sauce; then alternate layers of lasagna, sauce, cheese and egg mixture and Mozzarella cheese until baking pan is filled.
Top with sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, or until cooked thoroughly.

title: j'omlet(jerry's omelet)
directions: Single Egg J'Omlet:
Preheat skillet with vegetable oil or margarine.
Beat in a single egg with a dash of pepper and a splash of milk.
Spread some margarine on one side of a slice of bread.
Pour the egg batter into the skillet and place slice of bread with the spread up.
When the egg is cooked, turn it over for the bread to toast.
Add a slice of cheese, cut up in strips. Allow cheese to melt. Remove from pan and add maple syrup, if desired.

title: country chicken
directions: Sprinkle the chicken with the salt and pepper.
Brown in the oil.
Combine the tomatoes, thyme, garlic powder and celery salt; pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer for 45 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: nacho dorito casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown hamburger. Chop and saute your onions and bell peppers in a little butter. Bring to a boil your can soups and enchilada sauce, stirring often. Pour the bag of nacho chips in a 13 x 9 inch oblong pan, then layer your hamburger, then onion and pepper, then pour the sauce over all. Put cheese slices on top. Bake until cheese melts, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add cake mix, water and flour; stir and knead.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll dough out on floured board into 1/4-inch thick rectangle.
Top with brown sugar, cinnamon, nuts and raisins.
Roll up, beginning at wide side.
Seal well by pinching edge of dough into roll.
Cut into slices about 1 to 1 1/2-inches thick and place on buttered baking dish.
Let rise in warm place for about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: baked catfish fillets
directions: Salt and put lemon pepper on each fillet.
Place in buttered casserole and spread 2 tablespoons Ranch dressing on each fillet. Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese on each piece.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crab pita salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve on pita bread cut in quarters or use as a dip.

title: mexican sauce
directions: Heat oil in saucepan, add onion and pepper.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients, simmer for 45 minutes, serve with chicken.
Yields 6 cups of sauce.

title: pamela's spiral salad
directions: Cook spirals according to pkg. directions. Drain & cool immediately under cold running water until no heat is left in them. Slice
the olives, mince the garlic, dice & chop the onions, tomatoes and pickles. Mix all together adding shredded
cheddar cheese and bag of baby peas. Mix well and add salt, pepper and dill to taste.

title: italian bread peanut butter pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease deep 4-quart casserole. In saucepan, scald milk and cream over moderate heat.
Remove from heat and set aside.
Lightly butter 1 side of each bread slice. Thickly spread peanut butter.
Arrange slices in casserole, peanut butter side up, overlapping slightly if necessary.

title: sparkling cranberry punch
directions: Mix in a large container or punch bowl and serve over ice.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: In large bowl blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Spray a loaf pan lightly with vegetable cooling spray; add fruit mixture.
Freeze several hours until firm.
(For individual servings: spoon mixture into paper cupcake foils and freeze on a cookie sheet.)

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice in cooking oil until light brown.
Add onion, tomatoes, chilies, celery, garlic, beef stock and tomato sauce. Stir.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil, then simmer until rice is soft and all moisture is removed.
Add water if needed.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line greased casserole with tortillas.
(Dip tortillas in chicken broth to soften.)
Layer chicken, onion and pepper, 2-inch layer of tortillas and rest of milk.
Top with tortillas and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in salt water 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Mix well.
Put in casserole dish and bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, celery salt, garlic powder and pepper into ground beef.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place meatballs in ungreased baking dish.
Stir together tomato sauce, 1 cup water and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meatballs.
Cover with foil. Bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
