title: homestyle scrambled eggs
directions: Beat eggs, salt and water. Melt margarine in 10 inch skillet over medium heat. Cook potatoes, zucchini and tomato in margarine, stirring occasionally, until hot. Pour egg mixture over vegetable mixture. As mixture begins to set at bottom and side, gently lift cooked portions with spatula so that thin, uncooked portion can flow to bottom, do not stir. Cook 3 to 5 minutes or until eggs are thickened throughout but still moist.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Add onion rings and green pepper.
Mix vinegar, sugar and salad oil.
Pour over beans and refrigerate 8 hours.

title: vegetarian tacos
directions: Mix kidney beans with cheese and lettuce (both shredded). Spoon mixture into 2 hard corn taco shells.
Top with 1 1/2 tablespoons sour cream and 2 tablespoons of salsa.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Cream together margarine, powdered sugar, milk, coconut and vanilla.
Drain cherries.
Place 1 cherry inside each tablespoon of dough.
Roll into a ball and roll in graham cracker crumbs. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: keaki's hoomao
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Prepare, bake and cool cake following package directions.
Trim bottom crust from cake.
Tear cake into bite size pieces.
Place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare pudding following package directions using 4 cups milk.
Stir in pineapple as pudding begins to thicken.
Pour pudding mixture over cake pieces.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Spread with Cool Whip to cover completely.
Garnish with toasted coconut, if desired.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: french bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Lay bread slices flat on a cookie sheet. Spread mixture over bread slices.
Heat in oven at 350° until bubbly and melted.

title: spaghetti hot dish
directions: Brown meat and onion. Sprinkle with salts and pepper. Add tomato soup and seasonings. Boil spaghetti. Drain (don't overcook). In crock-pot, layer spaghetti with cheese and meat sauce. Mix mushroom soup and 1 can of water and pour over the mixture in the crock-pot. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or cook in crock-pot on medium for 1 1/2 hours or until bubbly.

title: chicken gizzards in hot tomato sauce
directions: Wash gizzards and
remove
any fat.
Chop gizzards in 2 to 3 pieces.
Heat oil in large skillet and brown garlic.
Add gizzards and saute over medium-high heat for 15 to 20 minutes. Add red crushed
pepper,
bay
leaf and saute an additional 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cook on low heat for
2 to
hours.
To serve sprinkle with parsley, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.
This is good served with rice.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Fold margarine, sugar and eggs and cream until fluffy, then fold in sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together cake flour, baking powder and salt.
For topping, combine chopped nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Place 1/2 batter; sprinkle half of topping.
Add remaining batter and sprinkle the rest of the topping.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Flake.
Add bread crumbs and onion.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Combine with salmon mixture.
Put in greased 4 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes, until firm.

title: yum yums
directions: Mix cake mix, melted butter and 1 egg.
Spread into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; flare edges slightly.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put cottage cheese in mixing bowl and add unbeaten eggs.
Cut cheese and margarine into pieces and add to it.
Add spinach, flour and salt.
Stir.
Pour into well-greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken peachy salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions.
Cool mixture. Combine all ingredients in medium size bowl.
Toss lightly to coat and chill salad.
Can serve in lettuce cups and serve with nut bread, oatmeal bread or hard rolls.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crab casserole
directions: Stir milk into butter and flour and cook.
Add salt, horseradish, lemon juice, mustard, parsley, eggs, crabmeat and bread crumbs.
Place either in casserole or shells and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mystic punch
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Place in punch bowl (should be mushy).
Add 7-Up and Squirt.
Serves 50.
Approximate Cost:

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, cocoa, milk, butter and egg yolks and cook until thick.
Add vanilla and pour into cooked and cooled pie shell.
Beat egg whites and add 3 to 5 tablespoons sugar. Beat until stiff and mound on top of pie.
Bake until brown in 325° oven.

title: corn bread hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a 10 inch ovenproof skillet, cook the beef, onion and green pepper over medium heat until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in the soup, salsa, ketchup and steak sauce.
Prepare corn bread batter according to package directions; let stand for 2 minutes.
Spoon over beef mixture.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with parsley if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zuni corn soup
directions: Dice lamb into cubes; simmer in 3 cups of water until tender. Cut corn from cob and add to lamb with 3 cups more water (very hot).
Add chile and simmer until corn is tender.

title: potluck ham casserole
directions: Gradually add milk to mushroom soup, stirring over low heat to make smooth sauce.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, onion and pepper.
Arrange half of noodles, ham and sauce in greased 2 qt. casserole.
Repeat layers.
Top with toasted almonds.

title: easy cheese muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl; make well in center of mixture.
Combine egg and milk; add mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased miniature muffin pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove muffins from pans immediately and let cool slightly on wire racks.

title: carrot crunch casserole
directions: Cook
carrots
and
onion together, then mash.
Add egg and milk; beat thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and put in buttered
casserole.
Sprinkle
with additional butter and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip.
Puree avocado with lime juice, salt and pepper in blender.
Spread on bean dip.
In separate bowl, mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread on dip.
Layer with chopped scallions, then layer with black olives, then layer with cheese. Last garnish with tomatoes and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: carrot nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, vanilla and cinnamon.
Then gradually add flour, baking powder, carrots and nuts; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a bread loaf pan.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Use a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch Pyrex bowl.
Drain peaches.
Pour peach juice into Pyrex bowl.
Melt butter and add to peach juice. In a separate mixing bowl, mix sugar, flour and egg.
Blend together like coarse meal.
Chop peaches and add to butter and peach juice mixture.
Add flour, egg and sugar mixture.
Lightly press flour, egg and sugar mixture into juices.
Cook in oven at 325° until medium brown on top.

title: old-fashioned country corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Ladle into hot jar to 1/4-inch from top.
Seal jars.
Process in boiling water for 15 minutes.
Cool and test for seal.
Can also be kept refrigerated for a few weeks.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Heat soup and milk until smooth. Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add half of noodles to dish. Next, pour half of soup mixture on noodles; lastly, sprinkle half of the cheese cubes on top of cheese sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except topping, and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole pan.

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash well.
Salt inside and outside of chicken thoroughly. Brush outside with butter.
Place in roasting pan with water and cover.
Bake in 325° oven until done, approximately 20 minutes per pound.
Remove cover last half hour to brown.
Use chicken broth for rice dressing (hashwee), soups, etc.

title: chocolate crumb crust
directions: Mix well and press firmly on bottom of 9-inch round cake pan.

title: yellow angel food cake
directions: Boil together sugar and water until it will spin a thread. Pour syrup over beaten whites of eggs.
Beat until cool.
Add the egg yolks, well beaten.
Fold in flour, cream of tartar and vanilla.
Bake in oven for 1 hour.
Put cream of tartar in whites of eggs and vanilla in yellows.
Follow directions carefully.

title: papa's fried biscuits
directions: Heat a black iron skillet very hot with oil and spoon dough 1 spoon at a time until it fries.
Turn over after a few minutes. Great crust.

title: cranberry squares
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add cranberries.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes after bring poured into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: country chicken medley
directions: In oblong casserole, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Mix with potatoes, corn, salt, basil and nutmeg; set aside.
Mix cracker crumbs, salt and basil.
Melt 1/3 cup butter.
Dip chicken in butter then crumb mixture.
Cover with foil.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake for 10 minutes to brown top.
Very good.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well.
Spread in a baking dish.
Cover with bacon, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cover with sour cream and cheese.
Continue baking until cheese is completely melted.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter, flour and vanilla.
Add buttermilk. Divide between the two pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Prepare peaches, apricots, berries or other fruit in slices. Mix together the dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well. Pour over the melted butter.
Spread fruit over the batter and sprinkle sugar (about 1/4 cup) over the fruit.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brown.

title: pork roast barbecue(serves 10 to 12)
directions: Wrap roast tightly in foil.
Bake in an iron skillet for 8 to 9 hours at 225°.
Drain; remove bone and fat.
Shred meat. Combine sauces and vinegar if a sharper sauce is desired. Moisten meat with sauce and serve on buns.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: fresh rhubarb pie
directions: Place pastry in pan, refrigerate until ready to use.
Wash rhubarb, cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon and add to rhubarb.
Pour into crust and dot with butter, top with crust or lattice crust, bake 40 to 50 minutes or until brown and bubbly in 400° oven.
Frozen rhubarb can be used if fresh is not available.

title: three pepper meatball stew
directions: In a large bowl, combine ground beef, onion, oat bran, salt, pepper, 2 teaspoons soy sauce and egg; blend well.
For each meatball, use about 1 tablespoon mixture.
Shape into ball.
In Dutch oven or large skillet, brown meatballs in oil; drain.
Add rice and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until rice is tender, 13 to 14 minutes.
Stir in sugar, vinegar, peppers and pineapple juice.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until peppers are crisp-tender.
In small bowl, combine cornstarch and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; mix well. Stir into meatball mixture.
Cook until boils and thickens.

title: corn soup
directions: Grate or chop the corn; add the boiling water and onion.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Strain.
Melt the butter in top of a double boiler and stir in the flour.
Blend.
Add the milk and seasonings.
Stir in the strained corn pulp and cook for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: rhubarb crumb cake
directions: Combine and set aside the first 4 ingredients.
Cream shortening and brown sugar.
Stir in egg and blend well.
Combine sour cream and soda; add alternately with flour to the creamed mixture.
Stir in rhubarb and vanilla.
Put batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with the sugar-cinnamon-butter and nut mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy cheese potato bake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together in a 3-quart casserole.
Melt butter and stir in corn flakes.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: deluxe cheese fondue
directions: Mix half and half with flour and steak sauce.
In fondue pot, put butter with chicken bouillon cubes and onion.
Add cream mixture until it thickens, then add Swiss cheese and Parmesan cheese.
After this melts, add the white wine.
Serve hot!!!

title: black-eyes for new year's
directions: Soak red beans overnight.
Drain and rinse beans.
Return to saucepan.
Add 3 cups fresh water, black-eyed peas, bay leaf and salt.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 60 minutes or until peas and beans are tender.
Drain, discarding bay leaf.

title: broccoli-chicken soup
directions: Drain chicken; reserve liquid.
Chop chicken; set aside.
In a 3-quart pan, melt butter.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Stir in flour, mustard, salt, thyme and pepper.
Stir in milk and chicken broth all at once.
Cook and stir over medium heat until slightly thickened and bubbly.
Stir in vegetables, chicken and chicken liquid.
Cook and stir for 4 to 6 minutes or until vegetables are tender and soup is heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Process oats in a blender or food processor until ground like flour.
Beat butter and sugars at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until blended. Combine ground oats, flour, and next 3 ingredients.
Add to butter mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in chocolate and pecans. Drop dough by tablespoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in batches at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light golden brown.
Cool on racks.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer the first 5 ingredients in the order given.
Spread mayonnaise over the top, sealing sides.
Layer with bacon bits and cheese.
May be prepared and refrigerated a day before serving. Cover with foil and chill.
Don't toss.
Serve as is.

title: creole pork chops
directions: Brown 4 to 6 chops.
Pour sauce, made from ingredients, over them and simmer until tender.

title: apricot salad ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin in water and soften.
Drain apricots.
Sieve fruit and sugar in shallow pan.
Heat until sugar is dissolved. Stir gelatin into syrup until dissolved.
Mix lemon juice.
Cool. Stir in balance of ingredients.
Chill until firm in a 6-cup jello ring mold.
Serve with mayonnaise or favorite dressing on bed of greens.

title: hot pot beans
directions: Cook hamburger and bacon.
Mix with other ingredients.
Heat until hot.
Serve with corn bread.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Lay crescent rolls flat on an 11 x 17-inch pan.
Pinch together.
Bake according to directions.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, cream cheese and dressing.
Spread mixture on rolls. Sprinkle vegetables on top.
Refrigerate.
Cut into bars and serve.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Do not use mixer!

title: hearty pancakes
directions: Mix oats and buttermilk.
Refrigerate overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a hot, lightly greased griddle.
Turn pancakes when tops are covered with bubbles and edges are brown.
Serve hot with maple syrup.
Serves 4.
Low-fat.

title: pasta broccoli
directions: In saucepan, saute vegetables in oil.
Stir in chicken bouillon and bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese and spices.
Serve over your favorite pasta with a fresh salad.
Serves 4.

title: yummy yams - thanksgiving
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Top with a mixture of the last 4 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can put a layer of marshmallows on top for the last 5 minutes of cooking.

title: soft orange drop cookies
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients, then add the rest.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Make a glaze with powdered sugar, vanilla or orange juice.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
With mixer, beat cheese until fluffy, gradually beat in Eagle Brand until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Toss chips with flour; stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.

title: jeff's favorite lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large saucepan; drain.
Add sauce; simmer while preparing filling.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour, one-third at a time.
Add flavorings.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Blend shortening, butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
(For a softer, rounder cookie, add 1/2 cup flour.) Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on cookie sheet and bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool slightly before taking from cookie sheet.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Cut ribs into 2-rib serving sections; place meaty side up in roasting pan.
On each section place a slice of onion and lemon. Melt butter in saucepan; saute onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil and simmer for 15 minutes. Pour sauce over meat; roast in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until done, basting 4 or 5 times.
Or you may roast ribs for about an hour, then pour sauce over them and baste.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add onion and pepper, then cheese. Crush chips and sprinkle half of the package on top of the cheese.
Mix Ro-Tel and soups together. Spread on top of chips.
Top with the remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pickles
directions: Make
a cold brine of the first 4 ingredients.
To each jar, add
a
clove
of
garlic,
dill,
onion and one red hot pepper. Pack
with
cucumbers.
Pour
the cold brine over the cucumbers and
seal.
Put the jars in a cold water bath until they change color.

title: french onion soup
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Put in kettle with remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: mediterranean swordfish with potatoes
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, remove skin and bone from swordfish, if any. Cut swordfish into 1 1/2-inch chunks.
Cut each potato into quarters. Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch thick slices. Slice each radish in half.

title: quick spaghetti and hamburger casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and brown hamburger meat.
Arrange a layer of spaghetti in a buttered casserole dish.
Crumble part of the hamburger meat over spaghetti.
Repeat layers until meat and spaghetti are gone.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, until hot, at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: sausage meat patties with cream gravy
directions: Season, then form sausage meat into patties and fry slowly until brown in a frypan.
Remove from pan.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of fat; add flour and blend until smooth.
Gradually add hot water and bring to boiling point, stirring constantly. Then add milk and continue cooking until thickened.
Return sausage patties to sauce and reheat.
Serve on hot split biscuits. Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese 'n cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower as directed on package.
Meanwhile, in a medium saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onions until tender.
Stir in flour, parsley flakes, bouillon and garlic powder until well blended.
Add water and milk.
Cook until thickened.
Stir in cauliflower.
(Can substitute Green Giant frozen broccoli in cheese sauce.)
Serves 3 (1 cup) servings.
Contains 170 calories per cup.

title: chicken pie
directions: This delicious pie can be prepared early in the day, kept in a cool place and baked just before it is required.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in canned tomatoes and taco seasoning.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 can French fried onions.
In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1 cup Cheddar cheese and eggs; set aside.

title: italian style beans
directions: Prepare and cook green beans, cut in 1-inch pieces.
Cook beans, onions, olives and dressing, uncovered, over medium heat, just until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with tomato.
Makes 6 servings, 190 calories per serving.

title: miracle whip biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into biscuits.
Place in greased pan.
Cook at 450° until done, about 12 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter in a large pan.
Stir in garlic, green peppers and onions.
Cook until tender, stirring frequently.
Pour in tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Clean shrimp and add to sauce; cook 5 minutes.
Add Tabasco.
Serve with steamed rice.
Serves 6.

title: coffee cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan. Mix brown sugar and cinnamon and set aside. Place orange marmalade, by teaspoon, in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle nuts over marmalade.
Dip each biscuit in the melted butter and then in the sugar mixture.
Place biscuits over marmalade - standing on edge around side of pan, then in center of pan. Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture and melted butter on top.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: whacky cake
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together right in the pan you bake in (8 x 8-inch pan).
No greasing is required.
Then make 3 holes in the dry ingredients.
In the first hole put the oil; in the second hole, put the vinegar; in the third hole, put the vanilla.
Pour 1 cup cold water over all.
Stir well with a fork.
You may add chopped nuts if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Use any frosting you like.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together the butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Sift together the flour & salt.
Add to first mixture and blend well. Add chopped nuts.
Set aside to chill.
Form the chilled dough into 1 in. balls.
Place balls 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Do not allow to brown.
While still warm, roll the balls in powdered sugar.
Cool, then roll again in powdered sugar.

title: strawberry soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Add strawberries and boil 10 more minutes, stirring frequently.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine whipped cream and sour cream and fold into strawberry mixture.
Chill for 2 hours. Serves 6.

title: butterscotch pecan squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla, flour and nuts.
Spread on 16-inch long cookie sheet.
Bake at 370° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut when cool and place in an airtight container.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Blend the butter with the dill, lemon juice and a healthy amount of white pepper.
On a plate, shape the butter into 12 (1-inch) fingers.
Cover the plate with plastic wrap and refrigerate until completely firm, at least 2 hours.

title: great potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes in 2 quarts water until done, then scoop potatoes out of pot and mash with fork or mixer.
Put back into water; add remaining ingredients, except evaporated milk and flour. Beat together with fork and add to potatoes.
Cook on medium until thickened (about 45 minutes).

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Cut chicken breasts into chunks; brown with very small amount of olive oil.
Cook until done and brown.
Add about 2 tablespoons Dale's steak sauce, noodles, salad dressing and vegetables. Simmer for about 20 minutes with lid on.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and meat with onion, garlic and butter, then simmer 20 minutes in water/soup.
Thicken with tablespoon flour, then add sour cream.
Serve over noodles.
Garnish with paprika.

title: microwave rhubarb sauce
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the rhubarb, water and sugar. Microwave, uncovered, on High for 8 to 10 minutes, until rhubarb is tender, stirring once or twice. Stir in pudding mix until blended; cook 1 or 2 minutes, until thickened, stirring occasionally. Serve over ice cream or use any way you like.

title: *crazy crust pie*
directions: Melt margarine in a 6 x 9-inch glass dish.
Combine flour, milk and sugar.
Pour in with butter; do not stir.
Just pour in center.
Now, pour fruit in center of dish; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: olive mix
directions: Mix all together and keep in refrigerator.
Great on combination salad and meat sandwiches.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Pour boiling water over, stir until dissolved.
Combine cranberries, sugar, marshmallows, celery, and nuts.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour in 6-cup mold and chill overnight.

title: ann's cocktail sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate. Serve with fish, shrimp, crabs, oysters or crawfish.

title: baked rice with chiles and cheese
directions: Combine rice, sour cream and salt to taste, mixing well. Spread half of rice mixture in a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish (or spray with Pam).
Sprinkle half the Cheddar cheese on top. Add a layer of green chilies and top with remaining cheese. Spread remaining rice on top.
Dot surface with butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned rolled sugar cookies(the best)
directions: Combine shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg.
Add sour cream.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Roll out to about 1/4-inch thick and cut.
Sprinkle with sugar and bake on greased cookie sheet for about 12 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage au gratin
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Blend soup, milk and cheese.
Pour over cabbage; top with crumbs, mixed with butter.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: pickled squash
directions: Layer vegetables in bowl and sprinkle generously with salt. Let stand one hour.
Drain.

title: party punch
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve sugar in water.
Add juices. Refrigerate for 2 hours or until chilled.
Just before serving, stir in soda.
Yields 7 1/2 quarts.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and the milk together well.
Add lemon juice and vanilla.	Pour into graham cracker pie crust and put into the refrigerator.
Chill well before serving.

title: southern spoon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Pour 4 cups milk in the top of a double boiler.
Add 1 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a simmer but do not boil. Add cornmeal, stirring slowly and constantly.
Continue stirring until the mixture takes on a light consistency.
Add butter.
Stir until melted, then stir in eggs.
Allow mixture to come to a simmer, then remove from the heat.
Stir vigorously, then pour into a well-buttered 2-quart souffle dish.
Place in oven for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to between 400° and 425° and bake another 20 minutes.
Test with a straw.
If center is not firm, give it another 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: chicken marangot
directions: Heat a clove of garlic in 2 tablespoons each of olive oil and butter.
Brown chicken pieces in this mixture.
Remove chicken to a covered casserole.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to frying pan and lightly brown mushroom caps.
Add chopped tomatoes, white wine, salt and pepper.
Pour tomato-wine mixture over chicken pieces and cook in oven at 350° to 400° until the chicken is tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with white rice.

title: scallop casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 the butter; add flour and make smooth paste.
Add cream and vermouth and cook until sauce is thick.
Season. Saute mushrooms in 1/2 the butter for 3 minutes.
Add scallops and cream sauce.
Put in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pig out party mix
directions: Place in large roasting pan and mix thoroughly the first 6 ingredients.
Then melt oleo and bacon drippings.
Mix all sauces and seasonings.
Sprinkle over breakfast food mixture, a tablespoon at a time, and stir dripping mixture each time as seasoning goes to the bottom of the pan.

title: easy brownies
directions: Melt margarine in pan over low heat.
Add cocoa and stir to blend as butter melts.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat well together.
Stir in the margarine and cocoa mixture; add vanilla. Stir in flour.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, combine baking soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla extract.
Beat until creamy. Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oatmeal and butterscotch morsels.
Drop by tablespoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes for chewier cookie or 9 to 10 minutes for crispier cookie.

title: sweet muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Grease bottom of muffin cups or use paper muffin cups. Beat egg with fork. Stir in milk and oil. Blend dry ingredients; stir in egg mixture just until flour is moistened. Batter should be lumpy. Do not over mix. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown. Muffins will have gently rounded and pebbled tops. Makes 12 medium muffins.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil last 3 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour over other ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet.

title: white baked beans
directions: Mix all together.
Put in baking dish.
Lay bacon on top. Bake for 2 hours at 400°.

title: sherried artichoke chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasonings and brown in 4 tablespoons butter.
Arrange chicken in 2-quart casserole.
Add artichokes to casserole dish.
Add remaining butter, mushrooms and onions in frying pan.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: peanut butter camping bars
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to boil.
Add peanut butter and blend.
Remove mixture from the stove and add Rice Krispies. Press mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°, then turn off.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over rice mixture.
Melt chocolate in the oven and then spread.

title: potato candy
directions: Mash potato very fine.
Add butter; use wooden spoon.
Add confectioners sugar until stiff enough to roll.
Roll out like pie crust, but in rectangular shape.
Roll 1/3 of candy mixture at a time (easier to handle).
Roll on waxed paper or plastic wrap to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread with peanut butter.
Roll up like cinnamon rolls.
Wrap tightly in plastic wrap.
Put in refrigerator.
Slice when ready to eat.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Cut celery, carrots, green peppers and onions into 1 to 2-inch chunks.
Combine with tomatoes with juice and the green beans. Place in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Combine salt, sugar, tapioca and butter and top vegetables with this combination. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Lower heat to 325° and continue baking for 1 more hour.

title: easy mints
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Gradually add confectioners sugar.
May have to knead by hand.
Add extract and food coloring.
Roll in small balls.
Wait a few minutes, then flatten with a fork.
Leave out to dry (overnight).

title: gingerberry liqueur
directions: Combine berries, candied ginger, vodka and wine in a large jar with a screw-top lid.
Place in a cool, dark place for 1 month to steep.
Crush berries with a wooden spoon; steep for another 4 days.
Strain the liquid, pressing as much juice from the berries as possible.
Filter liquid through a coffee filter.
Boil sugar and water together until sugar is dissolved.
Cool.
Gradually stir into the liqueur, tasting for desired sweetness.
Pour into a clean, decorative bottle and age 3 weeks before using.

title: baked beans and more beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion.
Mix with all remaining ingredients and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: cinnamon blueberry jam
directions: Crush berries.
Measure 2 1/2 cups and place in a large pot. Add the sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Bring to a full rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in pectin.
Skim off foam.
Pour into hot jars. Leave 1-inch headspace.
Process 15 minutes in a boiling water bath.
Yields 4 half pints.

title: lime jello salad(country:  u. s.)
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with hot water; add marshmallows and dissolve. Add cold water.
Let mixture set (will take several hours).
Do not let mixture get too solid.
When set enough, mix with remaining ingredients, using mixture on low speed.
Fold nuts in last.
Refrigerate until solid.
May be used as a side dish or dessert.
Make this recipe early in the day, or day before.
Makes approximately 8 servings.

title: fluffy pudding frosting
directions: Pour the milk into a medium bowl.
Add pudding mix and sugar. Beat with a wire whisk for 1 to 2 minutes or until well blended. Stir in the Cool Whip, gently.
Spread on cake at once.

title: easy chicken
directions: In a large skillet spray Pam and saute pounded chicken breasts for about 5 minutes on each side (until pink is gone).
Remove from pan.
Chop the celery, onion and green pepper and saute in pan until onion is transparent.
Add can of stewed tomatoes and can of tomato sauce.
Sprinkle in tarragon and basil.
Heat until bubbly, about 10 minutes.
Return chicken breasts to the sauce and heat another 10 minutes or so.
Serve with or over rice.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan melt margarine.
Remove from heat. Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crackers.
Top with chocolate chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut.

title: city chicken and mushroom
directions: Bread city chicken and deep fry in oil.
Place the chicken in a casserole pan.
Pour 1 can cream of mushroom soup diluted with a little bit of water over top of the chicken; bake for 1 hour or until tender at 350°.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use 1 1/2 to 2 rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture to 1 cup hot water.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Mix all ingredients for 4 minutes. Pour batter in greased pan and bake for 50 minutes at 325°.
Take cake out of oven and punch full of holes with spaghetti fork and pour the sauce over the cake with large spoon, making sure to cover cake evenly with sauce.
(Use all the sauce.)

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, place lettuce, chopped onions, mushrooms and peas one layer at a time.
Mix yogurt, mayonnaise and cheese together and spread this mixture over top of the salad.
Chill (preferably) for 24 hours.
Toss well before serving.
Serves eight; 165 calories, eight grams of fat each.

title: fort edward chili
directions: Fry and chop bacon.
Fry onion and hamburg; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 package crescent rolls in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Be sure to pinch the seams together.) Separate egg.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk and vanilla until creamy.
(Save egg white the top.)
Spread cream cheese mixture evenly over crescent rolls.
Spread 2nd package of crescent rolls over cream cheese mixture.
Mix 1/2 cup (additional) sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Brush over top of crescent rolls.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or a little less if they look done.

title: samovar instant tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
To serve, mix 1 heaping teaspoonful to 1 cup hot water to taste.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: green pea salad
directions: Drain peas and combine peas with remaining ingredients.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix soups, rice and milk well.
Place chicken on top.
Slice butter on top of chicken.
Salt and pepper optional.
Cover with foil and bake an additional 1/2 hour or until chicken is golden brown.

title: pumpkin crisp
directions: Sprinkle the dry cake mix evenly on top of the first mixture. Spread the chopped nuts evenly on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle margarine on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers in large kettle.
Drain off fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients; simmer at least 15 minutes to allow flavors to blend.
This is a very mild chili.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peachy cheese pie
directions: Put on top of peaches.
Sprinkle on mixture of 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Peel, core and cook apples until soft.
In a large roaster, combine cooked apples, plus other ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour or more, until butter jells around edges.
Stir frequently. Process in hot jars for 5 minutes.

title: frozen pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Crush 40 Ritz crackers.
Mix with 1 stick softened butter/margarine.
Press into 9x13 pan.

title: turkey with mushroom sauce
directions: Saute onion, pepper and celery in 1/4 cup cooking oil until transparent. Add soup and water. Add turkey and all other ingredients except wine. Cook for 30 minutes. Stir in wine. Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and water and pineapple juice.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Put
in
a
x 13-inch pan and chill until set. When firm add topping.

title: crunchy celery skillet
directions: Cook and stir all except pimentos in oil in frying pan until celery is crispy tender, about 10 minutes or a little longer. Stir in pimentos.
Heat through and serve.
Enjoy.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a 3-quart saucepan. Bring mixture to a boil and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop on waxed paper or pour mixture into a greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pizza biscuits
directions: Press canned biscuits on cookie sheet.
(If the dough sticks, run hands under cold water.)
Put sauce on to preference.
Put cheese or other toppings on to taste.
Put in oven; bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Cool and enjoy!

title: decadent triple layer mud pie
directions: Mix chocolate and condensed milk until well blended. Pour into a large bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat with a wire whisk 2 minutes or until well blended. Spread over pudding in crust. Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate 3 hours.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: best fruit cake ever
directions: Before you start, sample the whiskey to check for quality. Good, isn't it?
Now go ahead and select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the whiskey again as it must be just right.
To be sure the whiskey is of the highest quality, pour one level cup into a glass and drink it as fast as you can.
Repeat. With an electric mixer, beat a cup of butter in a large fluffy bowl.
Add one teaspoon of thugar and beat again.
Meanwhile, make sure the whiskey is of the finest quality.
Cry another tup. Open the second wuart if necessary.
Add to arge leggs.
Two cups fried druit and beat until high.
If druit gets stuck in beaters, just pry it loose with a drewscriver.
Sample whiskey again, checking for tonscisticity.
Then sift 3 cups of salt or anything, it really doesn't matter.
Sample whiskey.
Sift 1/2 pint of lemon juice.
Fold in chopped butter and strained nuts.
Add one babblespoon of brown thugar or whatever color you find and mix well.
Grease oven and turn cake pan to 350°.
Now pour the shole mess onto the boven and ake.
Check the whiskey again and go to bed.

title: kraut salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and salt to a boil.
Let cool.
Cut up pepper and onion and mix with kraut and pimentos.
Pour sugar-vinegar mixture over kraut mixture.
Makes 1/2 gallon.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: poppy seed bundt cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes with hand mixer.
Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Drizzle icing on cake if desired.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients except flour.
Mix until creamy, then add flour 1/2 cup at a time.
Batter will be moister than normal but you should still be able to form 2-inch balls from batter.
If it sticks to your fingers, add a little more flour to batch.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Put chicken and 3 whole stalks of celery in a large pot and cover with water.
Cook until chicken is done (save broth).
Cook spaghetti in broth.
Debone chicken.
Saute 3 stalks of chopped celery and 1 small onion (chopped) in 1/2 stick of margarine until tender.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
Cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Drain spaghetti.
Add chicken, cheese mixture and spaghetti.
Put in oven and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: sparkling fruit bowl
directions: Finely shred 1 teaspoon orange peel from 1 orange; set aside. Peel and slice the 2 oranges cross-wise.
In a glass serving bowl, arrange orange slices on bottom.
Top with 3 layers of desired fruits.
Cover and chill before serving, if desired. Combine the reserved orange peel, carbonated water, honey and lemon juice; chill this separately.
Pour over fruit bowl and serve at once.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with sugar.
Meanwhile, cream sugar, salt and Crisco; add egg.
Next, add dissolved yeast and additional 2 cups water.
Add flour gradually until dough is no longer sticky.
Cover and let raise until doubled in a warm place. Punch down and form rolls.
Spray baking sheets.
Let rolls raise, covered, until doubled.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake 8 to 12 minutes or until browned.

title: cottage cheese roast
directions: Mix together.
Put in greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: billy salad
directions: Using 1/2 of each ingredient, layer in a large, clear, straight-sided bowl as follows:
lettuce, carrots, peas, turkey, shells, cheese and egg slices.
Make sure you can see all layers through bowl.
Use same order and repeat layers.
Serve as a side dish or entire meal.

title: raw cranberry sauce
directions: Put cranberries, apples and orange peel through food chopper. Cut oranges in small sections with scissors and add sugar.
Stir mixture well and set in refrigerator.
Serve as a sauce or as a dessert in little parfait glasses.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix buttermilk and oil together. Add flour and mix. Grease cookie sheet. Roll biscuits into balls with hands. Place them on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° until browned. Serve hot.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Add to water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/4 cups liquid. Wash chicken.
Pat dry.
Coat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
While chicken is browning, combine remaining liquid ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook until boiling, stirring constantly.
Stir in cornstarch, which has been mixed with a small amount of water or pineapple juice, to make a thin paste.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Pour over chicken, which has been placed in a casserole dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Add pineapple and green pepper.
Cook, uncovered, for an additional 30 minutes longer.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Combine all and bring to boil.
Simmer for 5 minutes and cool, pour over eggs.

title: chopped steak
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and chili
powder.
Add other ingredients.
Cook very slowly.
Simmer for at least 2 or 3 hours. The longer it cooks the better the flavor. Serves 20.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Melt cream cheese in mushroom soup in microwave or over a double boiler.
Add mayonnaise and onions.
Chill several hours.

title: mandarin orange chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, lemon juice, onions and salt.
Chill well.
Add salad dressing, grapes, oranges and almonds.
Serves 6.

title: cafe suisse mocha
directions: Put all
ingredients
in blender.
Cover and process at liquefy until
well
blended.
Use one level tablespoon of mix with 6 ounces
of boiling water for each cup.
Stir.
Makes 16 servings.

title: pizza crackers
directions: Spread rounds with ketchup or sauce and top with pepperoni slices.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake on cookie sheet 3 to 5 minutes at 400°.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill.

title: seven layer dip
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef.
Set aside to drain and cool to room temperature.
Spread the beans into the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch serving tray that is about 1 1/2 inches deep. Sprinkle 2 cups of shredded cheese on top of beans.
Sprinkle beef on top of cheese.
Spread sour cream very slowly on top of beef. Spread guacamole on top of sour cream.
Pour salsa over guacamole and spread evenly.
Sprinkle remaining shredded cheese.
Sprinkle black olives, tomatoes and green onions on top.
You can serve this dish immediately, or refrigerate it overnight and serve cold. I think it tastes better at room temperature.

title: squash with pecans(nutritious)
directions: Spray 6-cup casserole with nonstick spray, add squash, stir in 2 tablespoons butter, 1/4 cup pecans, the sugar substitute, salt and nutmeg.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.
Dot with diet margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.
Each serving amount:
One portion equals 1 vegetable and 1 fat. Cholesterol 0, carbohydrate 7 g, fat 5 g. calories 68, protein 2 g, fiber 3 g and sodium 786 mg.

title: sunshine dills
directions: Put washed cucumbers in jars with dill and garlic cloves. Pour hot liquid, consisting of the vinegar, water and canning salt over the cucumbers that have been packed in jars.
Seal jars and set out in sun for 5 days.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix in blender, adding honey, vinegar, lemon juice, mustard, oil, poppy seed, salt and onion if desired.
Blend until oil disappears.

title: fried okra or squash
directions: Use fresh or frozen.
Slice if fresh.
Dip in water; then coat real good with House-Awtrey seafood breader mix.
Drop in hot grease and deep-fry until golden brown.

title: all-purpose meat sauce
directions: For spaghetti or lasagna, add 1/2 teaspoon oregano and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.

title: old fashioned carrot soup
directions: In large heavy pot, over medium-high heat, bring broth, carrots, onions, celery and parsley to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Cool slightly.
In blender container or food processor, blend mixture in batches until smooth; set aside.
In same saucepan, melt margarine; blend in flour.
Stir in carrot mixture and milk. Cook, stirring occasionally until heated through.
Garnish with additional parsley, if desired.

title: chicken with peanuts
directions: Rub broilers
with
salt,
pepper
and butter and roast about 30 minutes	at
Fry peanuts in olive oil; combine oil and peanuts
with
consomme and sherry.
Whirl in an electric blender. Pour sauce over broilers and continue roasting, covered, for 30 more minutes.
Serves 4.

title: christmas tea
directions: Syrup:
Combine 1 quart water, sugar, cinnamon sticks, whole cloves and allspice.
Boil rapidly for at least 10 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Simmer 15 or 20 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza loaf
directions: Use 1/2 teaspoon oil and brown the turkey.
Crumble turkey and add onion.
Sprinkle mixture with 1 tablespoon flour and stir quickly to combine.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Add bell pepper, basil, fennel seed and oregano.
Bring to boil.
Cook 1 minute. Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and transfer turkey mixture to pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
In small bowl, mix egg and remaining flour and oil along with the milk and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Pour batter over turkey loaf and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake until loaf is puffed and golden, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; stir often. Reduce heat and simmer until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Pour mixture over vegetables and refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Yield: 10 to 12 servings.

title: gekochtes sauerkraut(cooked sauerkraut, basic recipe)
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with warm water in colander, drain well. Place in heavy saucepan or pot with the butter and seasonings (salt, pepper, caraway seed, juniper berries, onion, apple, whatever you like).
Cover pan tightly, simmer over lowest heat 15 to 30 minutes.
Add liquid (omit salt if bouillon is the liquid). Cook 30 minutes to 1 1/2 hours longer, according to your taste. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry gelatin salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Stir to dissolve.
Add strawberries and pineapple (including juice) to jello.
Place 1/2 of mixture into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Place in freezer until set.
Spread sour cream on top of set jello.
Add remaining jello mixture.
Chill.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and oregano.
Drain fat from meat.
Add sauce, paste and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes. Cook noodles; drain.
Layer in lasagna pan noodles, sauce and shredded cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese (3 layers).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, until cheese melts and starts to bubble.
Remove from oven and let set for a while before cutting.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple and add pineapple liquid to boiling water. Dissolve jello and add ice cubes to chill.
When jello has thickened, gradually add Cool Whip until smooth.
Stir in oranges, pineapple, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into 6-cup mold. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Unmold.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cut wieners in pieces and add other ingredients.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes.

title: chicken wings drums
directions: Add all ingredients and boil chicken for 1/2 hour in large pan. Soak over night.
At 400 for 15 minutes.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Meanwhile, in 1-quart saucepan, combine water, peanut butter, soy sauce and crushed red pepper.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Add snow peas; cook 1 minute or until sauce is smooth and snow peas are tender-crisp, stirring constantly.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and chill; preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 8 minutes.
You can roll these up, freeze and bake later.

title: basil chicken breast
directions: Brown chicken breasts in olive oil and butter.
Remove from pan.
Put in casserole dish.
Place fresh basil leaves on top of breasts, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 4.

title: pasta with oil and garlic
directions: Cook pasta al dente.
In a large frying pan; saute garlic in olive oil.
Add parsley.
Add cooked pasta to frying pan; immediately, while pasta is still hot, toss thoroughly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with a few basil leaves.
Serve with grated cheese and a glass of white wine.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook strawberries, sugar and cornstarch until thickened.
Then add strawberry Jell-O.
Cool.
Put in baked pie shell.
Cover with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: apple-cheese casserole
directions: Pour apples into bottom of a pan.
Mix the other ingredients together (easier to use your hands) and press mixture on top of apples.
Pour 1/4 cup whipping cream or milk on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheesy lasagna
directions: Prepare lasagna according to package directions; drain and set in cold water.
In large pot, combine Italian sausage, ground beef, onions and garlic.
Cook until sausage is no longer pink and onions are tender; drain.
Stir in the next 7 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Add topping and bake at 350° until crust is brown.

title: spicy orange chicken
directions: Combine water, onion, orange juice, ketchup, garlic, cinnamon, Tabasco sauce and salt and mix well.
Place chicken in large shallow baking dish.
Pour marinade mix over chicken.
Cover. Chill for 4 to 6 hours.
Turn chicken occasionally.
Remove chicken from marinade.
Grill chicken until tender and juicy. Baste while grilling.

title: special k cookies
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil over high heat, stirring.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Stir in cereal and mix well. Spread mixture on a buttered cookie sheet and set aside to cool. Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together and stir until smooth.
Spread over top of cookies.
Let sit until chocolate is set.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 cups lukewarm water.
Melt butter; cream sugar and 3/4 cup butter in a large bowl.
Add beaten egg, then add dissolved yeast to creamed mixture.
Add flour and mix well.

title: holiday cut-out cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flavorings, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour and stir until well mixed.
Cover and chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour.
On lightly floured surface, roll out and cut with cookie cutter. Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for approximately 8 minutes.
Buttercream Icing goes well on top (just powdered sugar, vanilla and butter, creamed together).

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix together.
Marinate chicken for at least 1 hour.

title: texas straw hats
directions: In a large skillet, cook onions and green pepper in hot oil until tender, but not brown.
Add beef; brown lightly and drain off grease.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve on corn chips; top with cheese.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Slowly add scalded milk to beaten egg yolks.
Stir in sugar mixture.
Cook and stir in top of double boiler over boiling water until mixture coats the spoon. Remove from heat; add vanilla.

title: easy breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done; drain and crumble.
Mix cheese and sausage and sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs; blend in milk. Pour over sausage and cheese.

title: hot tuna sandwiches
directions: Split buns, fill with mixture and wrap in aluminum foil. Pierce foil, heat for 30 minutes at 350° in oven.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix popcorn, M&M's and salted peanuts in large bowl.
Melt marshmallows in oil and oleo and cook 2 minutes longer.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn.
Mix well.
Press firmly into well-greased tube pan.
Let cool.
Remove from pan.
Serve sliced.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: In
10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion
until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Add
potatoes;
stir
gently
to
coat.
Heat to boiling. Reduce
heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until hot
and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with bacon and snipped parsley.
Garnish with parsley sprig, if desired.

title: drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, nutmeg, vanilla and baking powder.
Mix soda with milk; add alternately with flour. Drop with soup spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake plain or sprinkle with sugar or cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Makes 5 dozen; contains 122 calories per cookie.

title: mushroom rice
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish and bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked red snapper and rice
directions: *Ask to have any spine bones removed.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Serve with white sauce or tomato sauce.
Serves 4.

title: seven layer dip(tex-mex)
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocado with lemon juice, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
In a separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Combine brown sugar, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Cool until lukewarm.
Beat until creamy and thick enough to spread.

title: chicken dumplins
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in 2 tablespoons Crisco.
Mix in sweet milk to make a soft dough. Knead well.
Roll thin on floured board.
Cut into strips.
Put in pan to dry for about 3 hours. Drop piece by piece into boiling chicken broth. Cook about 20 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together hamburg and rice.
Boil cabbage until leaves fall off; wrap hamburg and rice mixture in cabbage leaves and put in baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over top and pepper to taste. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: texas cake(1 cake)
directions: Add the ingredients that you have placed in the refrigerator to the contents in your large mixing bowl.
Pour into sheet pan. Bake at 350° for 23 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread sour cream in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cut up beef, Swiss cheese and sauerkraut.
Spread on top of sour cream.
Put rye cubes on top and dot with margarine (if desired sprinkle caraway seed on top).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate (very coarse slivers, 1 to 2-inches long) 5 or 6 Eastern potatoes (Idahos are very dry).
Mix ingredients.
Fry large tablespoon of mix in 1/8-inch corn oil or Crisco until brown on both sides (2 to 4 minutes each side).
Drain on paper towel.
Keep warm in 200° oven.

title: ole chili pie
directions: Prepare corn muffin mix following label directions.
Spread in greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 375° for 18 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: If plain flour is used, add 1 teaspoon baking powder, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon soda.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Place bread crumbs, cheese, mustard, paprika and pepper in a large plastic bags.
Shake to blend
well.
Brush chicken with mayonnaise on all sides.
Add one piece at a time to crumb mixture; shake to coat well.
Arrange on broiler rack so that pieces do not touch.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown and chicken is done and tender.

title: chicken pilaf
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture. Melt oleo in heavy skillet.
Add chicken and brown on both sides. Set aside.
Saute carrots and onion in drippings until tender.
Add rice and cook over low heat until lightly browned.
Add bouillon mixture and thyme, stirring well.
Arrange chicken pieces over rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook the sugar, cornstarch and water over medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Cool.
Place berries in pie shell; pour gelatin glaze over.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream to serve.
Easy and delicious.

title: spanish rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef.
Drain grease.
Set aside. Saute onions and green peppers.
Add to beef.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add well beaten eggs, vanilla and apples. Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add nuts to batter and bake at 350° to 400° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Glaze if desired.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Add two heaping teaspoons to a mug of hot water.
Stir and enjoy!

title: top-stove beans and meat balls
directions: Mix well ground beef, milk, bread crumbs, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
With wet hands, shape into 16 balls.
Brown balls in skillet with shortening and sliced onion.
Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.
Add mixture of baked beans, salt, catsup and mustard.
Cover and heat.

title: brown mountain cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and warm water.
Bake in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry pie
directions: Line pan with pastry dough.
Blend flour with 2 tablespoons sugar.
Cover bottom crust with mixture.
Add fresh cherries and sprinkle remaining sugar on top.
Place top crust on.
Crimp edges.
Cut slits in top to let out steam.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 425°.

title: broccoli spears with lime butter
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions on packages; drain. Place in serving dish.
Melt butter in small saucepan; stir in lime juice.
Pour over broccoli spears; season with salt and pepper. Serves 16.
Easy to cut in half for a smaller amount.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken bundles italian
directions: In a large skillet, cook chicken and onions in hot oil over medium heat until chicken is no longer pink and onions are tender. In a large mixing bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder, oregano, nutmeg and lemon juice. Stir in chicken and onions. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Lightly grease 8 (10 ounce) custard cups with some of the melted butter or margarine.
Line each dish with an eggroll wrapper. Divide chicken mixture among the 8 dishes.
Fold the ends of each wrapper over the top of the chicken mixture, sealing to make a bundle. Brush with remaining melted margarine or butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until tops are golden.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Fold pudding mix into whipped topping.
Fold in remaining ingredients; chill thoroughly.

title: corn bread pudding
directions: Put all together; mix.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vanilla custard ice cream
directions: Thoroughly mix sugar, salt and cornstarch; stir in 1 quart milk.
Heat to just steaming point.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg yolks; gradually add 1 cup of the hot mixture, beating constantly. Stir egg yolk mixture into remaining hot milk and bring to steaming point again.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and evaporated milk to hot custard.
Cool.
Fold in egg whites, beaten to stiff peaks.
Pour into 1 gallon freezer can.
Add remaining milk to fill can 3/4 full and freeze.
You may add 1 pint peaches or strawberries to this basic recipe.

title: creamed hamburger and cabbage
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in butter, breaking up meat.
Add chopped cabbage and saute lightly.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper, paprika, celery seed and milk.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Good served over rice or noodles.

title: escalloped cabbage or cauliflower
directions: Melt butter or oleo.
Them stir in flour until smooth.
Add milk.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese to melt.
Cook cabbage or cauliflower in salt water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Arrange alternate layers of cabbage or cauliflower and sauce in a greased 2-quart casserole, ending with sauce.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ken and betty's special party dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Serve with chips.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook potatoes.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour until smooth.
Add milk; stir until smooth.
Add mashed potatoes gradually.
Add ham and/or bacon or both.

title: catalina dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a quart jar and shake thoroughly. Chill.
Shake again before using.
Especially good on salads and can use as a dip with raw vegetables.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 teaspoons sugar and margarine together.
Add pretzels. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool.
Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over pretzels and refrigerate.
Mix together strawberry jello and boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries. Let set partially.
Spoon over cream cheese mixture and chill until completely set.
Serves 12.

title: spicy pork and beans
directions: Mix in large bowl and place into baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° (very spicy).

title: pizza sauce
directions: Stir all ingredients in small saucepan and simmer slowly about 20 minutes.
Makes enough for 3 (15-inch) pizzas.
Bake pizza about 25 minutes at 425°.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Cook bacon and drain; saute bell pepper and onions in bacon drippings (have cooked rice) and all cooked onion and bell pepper. Add stewed tomatoes and cook slightly.
Add crumbled bacon, rice and shrimp.
Turn heat to medium and cook for 5 minutes.
Turn to simmer for 10 minutes (cooks better in iron skillet with lid).

title: quick chicken
directions: Put into 13 x 9-inch baking pan as follows: rice, then chicken with meat side up.
Pour in soups and water.
Put onion soup on top.
Seal with foil and place in oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.

title: chili-cheese sandwiches
directions: Place 4 slices cheese on each of 4 slices bread.
Spread each with 1 teaspoon chili sauce.
Divide chilies equally among sandwiches.
Top with remaining slices of bread.
Beat milk, egg, cumin and salt with fork in 9-inch pie plate until smooth.
Dip both sides of sandwiches into egg mixture.

title: dark moist bran muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Combine others and add all at once to dry group.
Stir just enough to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 18.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes and onion in 3 cups water until done.
Drain and save 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Melt butter; add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Slowly add milk and reserved potato liquid.
Stir constantly over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Add pepper to taste.
Add potatoes and onions into liquid mixture.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mother hubbard's soup
directions: Cook beans in water until tender.
Add seasonings and vegetables and heat 30 minutes over medium heat.
A few minutes before serving, add milk and heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown onion and meat.
Add celery and bean sprouts.
Mix chicken broth or water with soy sauce, molasses, salt and pepper. Add to mixture in skillet.
Simmer until vegetables are just done. Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Stir in.
Cook until thickened and bubbly hot.
Serve over rice on warmed plates.
My mother, Elsie Pflaum Wood, served this often.

title: party slush
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water.
Add orange juice and lemonade frozen.
Add 5 cups water and whiskey.
Stir until frozen products are melted.
Pour into wide-mouthed container and freeze. To serve, spoon into glass and add chilled ginger ale and garnish with lemon and orange slices.

title: nut bread
directions: Mix all together and put in greased pan.
Let stand one hour, then bake one hour or until done.

title: fettucine with asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus on bias 1 inch.
Cook until done.
Cook fettucine.
Heat butter in pot fettucine was cooked in.
Add asparagus to fettucine.
Add salt, pepper, nutmeg, 2 tablespoons of cooking liquid and basil.
Serve hot with Parmesan cheese.

title: scalloped scallops
directions: In a shallow buttered baking dish, arrange fresh scallops in pieces about the size of a large grape and no deeper than 1 1/2 inches.
Over these sprinkle cracker crumbs of the round butter kind, Ritz or Crax, lightly buttered also, and work into the scallops, not too many crumbs.

title: broccoli mold
directions: Dice cream cheese; soften.
Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain; add cream cheese.
In a saucepan, pour 1/2 can chicken broth and sprinkle gelatin over it.
Heat until dissolved; stir in broccoli, mayonnaise, eggs, Tabasco and remaining 1/2 can chicken broth.
Refrigerate, stirring occasionally, until partially thickened.
Turn into 6 cup mold and chill until set. Serve with Sour Cream Dressing.

title: 9-layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients; save out a small amount of cheese and bacon bits to sprinkle on top of generous amount of Miracle Whip.
Chill until served.

title: cool lemon torte
directions: Mix shortening, egg, water, coconut and cake mix.
Pat dough into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees until golden.
(Crust is still soft when done.)
Cool.
Pour prepared lemon pie filling over crust.
Chill.
Spread with whipped cream; Chill.
Cut in squares.
(For thicker filling, make 2 pkg. lemon pie filling.)

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, oleo and vanilla until smooth.
Whip the cream or use Cool Whip; fold into mixture. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Bake for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: holiday drink
directions: Heat apple cider; add remaining ingredients and simmer for 1/2 hour or more.
Serves 12.

title: cheese crackers
directions: Blend ingredients; shape in a roll.
Chill it until firm, then slice thin and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: crock-pot stuffed pasta shells
directions: In large kettle, boil the pasta shells in salted water until tender (not mushy).
Drain and set aside.
In a skillet or saucepan, brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, bread crumbs, parsley and egg.
Stuff this mixture into pasta shells.
Pour 1 jar of sauce into slow cooker.
Arrange the stuffed shells on top.
Top shells with remaining sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook on low for 5 to 7 houors.
Yields 8 servings.

title: french-baked chicken
directions: Season chicken with next 3 ingredients.
Place in single layer in shallow baking pan.
Baste with French dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Baste with French dressing. Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer or until brown and tender. Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: garbage cake
directions: Tear up cake into small pieces in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Pour strawberries over cake pieces.
Line with bananas.
Spread pudding over bananas.
Top with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: pork chops diane
directions: Brown pork, then place in an 8 x 17 x 2-inch baking dish. Slice and set aside onion and pepper garnish.
Dice remainder and add to rice, tomatoes and sauce.
Pour around chops.
Add garnish. Bake at 375°, covered, for 35 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal-orange muffins
directions: Pour 1/2 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup orange juice over 1 cup oatmeal, let stand.
mix sugar and margarine; add eggs (mashed banana may be substituted for 1/2 cup white sugar).
Add powder, soda and salt to 1 cup flour.
Then fold into other ingredients. Add raisins.
Place in paper muffin lined pan using small measuring cup as dip.
Bake 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix lemon juice, oil and seasonings in baking pan.
Coat chicken in liquid mixture.
Bake 50 minutes for boned chicken or 30 minutes for boneless.

title: poor man's sausage
directions: Mix thoroughly and form into 2 or 3 rolls.
Wrap in tinfoil with shiny side towards meat.
Chill 24 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together orange juice powder, pudding and the juice from pineapple chunks.
Then add the remaining ingredients.
Chill.

title: roy's chili
directions: Combine the tapioca, sugar and 1 cup of the water in a saucepan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly. Remove from burner.
Blend in the orange juice until melted.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cups water.
Cool 20 minutes.
Stir, cover and chill thoroughly.
Prepare desired fruit and cut into bite size pieces.
When soup is chilled, add the fruits and lemon juice. Serves about 8 hungry teenagers.
The recipe is easily doubled or tripled.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in skillet.
Holding a tortilla with tongs, dip each in hot oil 5 to 10 seconds, or until limp.
Drain on paper towels.
Add more oil if necessary.
Combine chicken, chilies, onion and salsa; spoon about 1/4 cup chicken mixture on tortilla.
Roll up.
Place tortillas, seam side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover; spread cheese on top.
Bake 5 minutes longer, or until cheese melts.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Melt chocolate in a double boiler over low heat.
Stir in cheese until smooth and well mixed.
Add vanilla and salt.
Add sugar, about 1/2 pound at a time.
Mix well after each addition.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix all ingredients, except popcorn.
Bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 teaspoon butter flavoring and 1 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popped corn and stir until corn is coated.
Put in 200° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: six week muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over 2 cups bran. Add shortening and let stand while gathering other ingredients. Mix rest of bran with sugar, eggs and buttermilk in large bowl. Combine flour, soda and salt. Combine all ingredients. Bake as needed at 400° for 20 minutes. Mixture will keep 4 to 6 weeks, covered, in refrigerator. Makes 6 dozen muffins.

title: cookies 'n' cream cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 8 or 9-inch round cake pans.
Combine all cake ingredients except cookies at low speed until moistened; heat 2 minutes at highest speed.
Gently stir in crushed cookies.
Pour batter into prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pans. Cool completely.

title: golden nuggets
directions: Bring to boil sugar, oil, mustard, soup and vinegar.
Layer onion, carrots and peppers.
Let set overnight.
Cover with Saran Wrap.

title: lula paste
directions: Blend cheese, onion and pimento.
Mix rest of ingredients. Store in refrigerator.

title: tuna cakes
directions: Mix bread, tuna, egg, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and salt. Shape mixture into three firm patties.
Fry over medium heat until golden brown on both sides.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box; bake.
Immediately after
removing from oven.
Poke cake full of holes with an ice pick.
Mix
Jell-O,
using
the
hot water only.
Pour Jell-O over cake, allowing it to soak in.
Let cake cool.
top with Cool Whip. Chill.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel or scrub potatoes.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in a baking dish.
Fan them slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter. Sprinkle with herbs.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake potatoes another 10 to 15 minutes, until lightly browned and cheese is melted.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt butter, chocolate and peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Put powdered sugar in large Ziploc bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake.

title: palascinta(pancakes with cheese)
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add gradually to flour mixture, beating to a smooth batter.
Spoon 3 tablespoons of batter to hot greased 7-inch skillet, tilting pan so batter is distributed to edges (very thin).
Brown lightly on both sides.
Continue until batter is used up.
Stack on plate. Spread with Ricotta cheese and 5 eggs which you mix together as the filling.
Roll up and place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Heat in 300° oven for approximately 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Beat melted Crisco, sugar, milk, cocoa, salt and vanilla together and cook for 2 minutes.
Cool for 1 minute.
Add oats and nuts and peanut butter.
Spoon onto waxed paper (cookie size) and allow to cool.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crust:
Use 2 of the 3 rows of cookies.
Crush them.
Add the melted butter.
Pat down in the bottom of pan or dish.

title: scalloped corn and oysters
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in a buttered baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all together. Bake 35 minutes at 350°, uncovered. Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Fry sausage and drain.
Place crescent rolls flat on bottom of glass casserole dish.
Smear butter on bottom of dish.
Pinch rolls together.
Put sausage on top of crescent rolls, then grated cheese on next.
Make batter with egg, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour on top of casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: mock menudo
directions: Saute pork chops and dice.
In large sauce pan combine water, bouillon cubes, pork, chili powder, Italian seasoning, pepper and onion flakes. Simmer covered for 1 hour.
Drain and rinse hominy. Add to mixture and simmer 1/2 hour more.

title: mile high chowder
directions: Bring broth to a boil, add barley and cover.
Simmer 12 minutes or until tender.
In another pan, melt margarine and cook mushrooms and peppers 5 minutes, sprinkle with flour cook 1 minute.
Add milk, bring to simmer over high heat, stir in thyme, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 10 minutes.
Stir barley mixture into soup, simmer uncovered 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Mix together all ingredients and cook until thickened (approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
If you want this hotter, add 2 more hot peppers.
Yields 6 pints.

title: pan roasted corn salsa
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in heavy large skillet over high heat; add corn. Saute until light brown; cool. Add remaining 3 tablespoons olive oil, tomato and remaining ingredients to corn in bowl. Toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken, debone and cut into bite size pieces, reserving chicken broth.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth.
Add remaining ingredients and top with cheese.

title: tu tu's cabbage(hawaiian for grandmother)
directions: Remove center of cabbage;
fill with ground beef, mixed with onion,
salt
and pepper.
Tie cabbage in cheesecloth and almost cover
with
water.
Add bay leaf.
Simmer about 1 hour or until done.
Serve with melted butter.

title: lemon-cheese bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix the cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup.
Pat the remainder crumb mixture in the bottom of an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix together the first four ingredients.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, remove from pans and prick with a fork.
Pour pineapple juice (drained from pineapple in icing) over layers.

title: new jersey salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water and dissolve in boiling water. Add sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice, tarragon vinegar, lemon juice and salt.
When thickened, add cucumber and pineapple which have been chilled and drained.
Pour into individual molds and chill. Turn out on lettuce leaves and arrange on platter.

title: wheat germ and raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat together the egg, milk and oil. Combine dry ingredients; add to egg mixture.
Stir until just moistened.
