Add raisins.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 9 muffins.

title: lazy jello salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, Cool Whip and jello.
Add fruit and chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, milk and eggs.
Melt shortening and add last.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
This makes 9 servings.
Spray iron skillet with Pam before adding corn bread mixture.

title: cherry veggie dip
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cherries, Blue cheese and walnuts. Stir in sour cream and mayonnaise; mix well.
Chill about 1 hour to blend flavors.
Serve with vegetable dippers, such as celery, carrots, cauliflower, broccoli, green or red peppers.
(Also can include crackers.)
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: chicken marsala
directions: Melt butter and saute the mushrooms and onion at medium-low heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture is nearly dry.
Set aside to cool.

title: barbecue sauce for pork or beef
directions: Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over shredded leftover meat.
Best if sits a few days, then warm it up and serve on sandwich rolls.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter in large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one. Gradually add sugar and cream until fluffy.
Stir in flour by hand, then frosting mix and nuts.
Pour batter into greased (Bundt) pan or 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 2 hours.
Remove from pan and cool completely before serving.
(Since this cake has a soft fudgy interior, test for doneness.)

title: hawaiian baked beans casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Saute onion and pepper.
Add to all the other ingredients with hamburger.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: killer bread
directions: Preheat broiler.
Mix mayonnaise, Parmesan and garlic in large bowl to blend.
Arrange bread, cut side up, on a large cookie sheet.
Butter bread.
Broil until crisp and brown.
Spread Parmesan mixture on both halves.
Broil again until just browned. Serves 12.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add sugar, melted Crisco, warm water and salt.
Add flour.
Place in greased pan to rise until double in bulk.
Make into rolls and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: clam chowder
directions: Mix all together in crock-pot; let cook all day on low.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with crusty rolls or bread sticks.

title: fig preserves
directions: Boil water and sugar for about 5 minutes.
Place peeled figs and lemon slices in the syrup.
Cook until figs are transparent and syrup is thick and pink, about 25 to 30 minutes.
Put in jars, but let cool before putting lids on.

title: sombaro dip
directions: Combine and place in baking dish.
Top with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chocolate pinwheels
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla and unbeaten egg yolk. Fold dry ingredients lightly into mixture alternately with milk. Divide dough into two parts.
Mix melted chocolate into one part. Chill both 10 minutes.
Roll or pat white dough to thin rectangular sheet.
Pat chocolate part on top of white to within 1/2 inch of edge.
Roll like jelly roll.
Put in waxed paper and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Cut in thin slices.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen small cookies.

title: wayne's miracle custard pie
directions: Combine ingredients except coconut in blender.
Cover; blend about 10 seconds (do not overblend).
Stir in coconut.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 40 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean. Cool, then chill.
As the pie cools, it will make its own crust.

title: cheesy-olive appetizers
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Spread about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture on each muffin half.
Broil 2 minutes or until cheese melts; cut each half into quarters.
Serve warm. Yield:
48 appetizer servings.

title: south carolina chow chow
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients fine or force through food chopper using medium blade.
Put in kettle.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bring to boil and simmer, stirring occasionally, 15 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Pour into 4 hot, sterilized pint jars and seal.
Process in water bath 5 minutes.

title: scott's shrimp salad
directions: Boil shrimp. Cool; chop up in small pieces. In a large bowl whisk miracle whip until smooth. Add onion, celery, parsley, salt, and pepper. Mix well. Fold in shrimp.

title: cheese sausage squares
directions: Melt the 3 cheeses in a double boiler or microwave.
Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix sausage into the melted cheese.
Add the jalapeno peppers to this mixture.
Line a 11 x 7-inch pan with waxed paper.
Pour in mixture.
Chill until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: mock lobster roll
directions: Mix everything but rolls.
Chill to blend flavors.
Serve in hot dog rolls.

title: west indies yellowbird
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shake well, pour into a tall glass with ice cubes and decorate with pineapple ring, maraschino cherry and orange slices.

title: scrod provencale
directions: Heat one tablespoon oil in iron skillet.
Saute onions and sliced celery until transparent.
Add sliced garlic and oregano or herbes de provence.
Simmer several minutes.
Add stewed tomatoes and simmer, uncovered until slightly thickened.
Place fish fillets on sauce; cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: easy german chocolate cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add shortening and mix until crumbly.
Add 1 1/8 cups milk.
Beat. Add eggs and beat.
Add 1 cup milk and vanilla and beat well. Fold in melted chocolate.
Pour into 3 greased cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with Coconut Frosting.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place all dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Add wet ingredients; mix on medium speed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: Wash livers and drain.
Heat chicken fat and saute 2 large chopped onions and chopped garlic just until brown and soft.
Add chicken livers; lower heat and cook until well done, but still soft.
Set to the side and cool 30 minutes or longer.
Put livers and boiled eggs through a meat grinder.
Be sure to add all the drippings through the grinder.
In a large bowl, put the liver mix; add salt, pepper, sugar and the small chopped onion.
Form into a ball and roll in fresh parsley.
Best if made at least 1 day ahead to season.
Serve with crackers.

title: strawberry margaritas
directions: Mix cider with 1/4 cup sugar, lemon juice, rind and spices. Let stand until sugar dissolves.
Combine milk and cream, then add to cider mixture, beating with electric beaters until frothy. Beat egg whites stiff; add remaining 1/4 cup sugar gradually. Fold egg whites into cider/milk mixture.
Chill until very cold. Pour into punch bowl.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sausage dressing
directions: Brown sausage with onion; drain fat.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch dish at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: white bean `n' ham soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the carrots and onion in butter. Stir in the water, ham, seasonings and beans. Cook over medium heat until heated through. Discard bay leaf before serving. Yields 6 servings (small).

title: beef stew
directions: Sprinkle meat with garlic, salt and pepper.
Mix in flour. Heat Crisco in 3-quart Dutch oven.
Sear meat until browned.
Add to pot:
potatoes, carrots, celery and onions, then beef broth, water, salt, basil and bay leaf.
Cover tightly, bake 2 hours at 350°.
When done, thicken by adding mixture of flour and water, 1 teaspoon of Kitchen Bouquet.
Bring to boil on top burner of stove. Stir frequently.
Serve with crunchy bread, salad and fruit.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape with hands.
Put in pan and cook at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Cook bacon in a skillet; remove bacon and break into pieces. In same skillet, cook onion in bacon grease until browned. After browning the onion, pour off most of the bacon grease. Add the bacon, beans, brown sugar and ketchup to the skillet. Stir well, cover and simmer slowly for a few minutes or combine all ingredients in a baking dish and bake in oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush
Oreos
and mix 1/2 stick butter and 2/3 Oreos in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick butter and powdered
sugar
until
smooth.
In
separate
bowl,
mix pudding and milk with vanilla.
Mix everything together except Cool
Whip. Spread
over
crusts.
Put
Cool
Whip over that; sprinkle rest of cookies on top and chill.

title: ole time sweet potato pie
directions: Peel
sweet
potatoes and slice longways about 1/4-inch thick. Cook
in
small amount of water until half done.
Line an
8 x 8-inch pan, bottom and sides, with homemade pie crust. Lay potatoes
crisscrossed
in pan.
Add margarine, allspice, sugar and
water.
Cover
with
pie crust.
With sharp knife, slit
the crust
several
times.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes until crust is brown.

title: apple salad(good)
directions: Whip the Dream Whip and add salad dressing, sugar and pineapple juice.
Combine all ingredients and chill.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mozzarella spread
directions: Stir all ingredients together and use.

title: cabbage casserole(takes the place of stuffed cabbage.)
directions: Wash and prepare cabbage by chopping into large pieces and put on bottom of a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Brown meat and onion and pour off fat.
Add rice, salt and pepper.
Pour meat mixture on top of cabbage.
Cover with soup and water.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 7.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix together the corn, milk and eggs.
Add cracker crumbs, butter, salt and pepper.
Pour this mixture into a greased casserole.
Sprinkle more cracker crumbs on top.
Dribble melted butter on top (about 1/2 cup).
Bake at 350° until center of casserole is firm (knife comes out clean).

title: mawmaw's boiled custard(club member: ben steadman)
directions: Heat milk in large double boiler.
While milk is heating, beat 8 eggs.
Add 2 cups sugar and 4 tablespoons flour, already mixed together, to 1 cup of hot milk.
Pour mixture in double boiler with rest of milk.
Cook until thick, constantly stirring.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Do not let custard boil.
Strain or blend in blender if desired.
Let cool.
Delicious served for dessert or used in recipes calling for custard base.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together. Use 4 Tbsp. of mixture per 1 cup of hot water.

title: old time chess pie
directions: Soften butter to room temperature, beat in sugar and eggs.
No need to cream sugar and butter, unless you are the kind that likes to revive the pleasure of making mud pies.
Sprinkle in cornmeal, vanilla and vinegar, mix well.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell (8 or 9 inch).
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until filling is set.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix altogether; fry in 3 tablespoons of margarine in frying pan.
Makes 6 to 9 patties.

title: easy chicken salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Toss with chicken, almonds and celery.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve on salad greens.

title: white sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour mixed with seasonings.
Stir until well blended.
Pour on milk gradually, while stirring constantly. Bring to boiling point.
Boil for 2 minutes.
Yield:
2/3 cup sauce.
Temperature:
Boiling.
Time:
2 minutes.

title: spicy pot roast with dumplings
directions: Slowly brown meat in hot fat.
Add the next 8 ingredients. Cover; cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours, or until tender.
Remove meat and keep hot.
Spoon dough (made from Bisquick and milk) into boiling liquid.
Follow directions on Bisquick box.
Serve with green beans.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour graham cracker crumbs over melted butter.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut over cracker crumbs. Sprinkle chocolate chips over coconut, then add butterscotch chips over the chocolate chips.
Sprinkle pecan pieces over the butterscotch.
Pour milk over layers evenly.
Cover with coconut. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Best cut when still hot.

title: saucy steak
directions: Beat steak; roll in flour.
Brown steak.
Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat until meat is tender.

title: marinated slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion, pepper and carrot.
Set aside. Mix together vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed, salt and turmeric and bring to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture.
Store in refrigerator 24 hours before serving (will keep for a month). You can use sugar substitute rather than sugar.

title: fun taco cups
directions: Brown meat, drain fat, add seasoning mix. Prepare as directed on package. Press biscuits onto bottom and up the sides of a medium muffin pan. Fill with seasoned meat. Bake at 400 for 15 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake 2-3 minutes.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie(diabetic)
directions: Pie Crust:
Combine flour and salt in medium bowl; cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing with fork until pastry just holds together.
Form dough into ball.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
On floured surface, roll pastry to 11 inches diameter. Ease pastry into 9-inch pie plate.
Trim and flute edges.
Pierce bottom with tines of fork.
Bake at 400° until browned, about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta and drain well.
Cut chicken in bite size pieces and saute in butter.
Remove and add onion and garlic.
Combine chicken, pasta, mushrooms, onion, soup and sour cream.
Turn into large casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 300° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove foil and continue to bake for an additional 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit cocktail cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add fruit cocktail, raisins and nuts.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix. Drop by spoon onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until done and very lightly browned.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together, then add to first mixture and mix well.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Add bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add and blend well.
Add nuts or wheat germ.
Bake in a greased and floured loaf pan at 375° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: lemon-herb chicken
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Toss with chicken nuggets. Brown chicken on all sides in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until tender.
Serve over yellow or white rice.

title: party pizza wedges
directions: Mix hot sausage and cheese.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze, then wrap.
Or bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cut into fourths.

title: broiled pork chops
directions: Prepare pork chops in Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Add garlic powder to each slice.
Place on broiler pan. Put a pat of butter on each slice.
Broil until tender.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan (shape into a loaf).
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, add remaining ingredients and stir.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet about 10 minutes at 375°.
Cookies will look soft when removed from oven.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; set aside.
Layer Tater Tots, soup, vegetables and tomatoes.
Add beef and onions on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Just before done, add cheese on top and return to oven until cheese melts.

title: butterscotch pinwheels
directions: Melt chocolate chips and 2 tablespoons Crisco in double boiler over boiling water.
Add sweetened condensed milk, flour and the vanilla.
Spread in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan which has been greased lined with wax paper and greased again.
Bake at 325° for 8 minutes.
Immediately turn chocolate base out onto a towel which has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Melt 1 cup butterscotch chips and 2 tablespoons in top of double boiler over boiling water.
Spread over chocolate base and sprinkle with the 1/2 cup chopped walnuts.
Roll up, starting with the 15-inch side. Wrap and store in refrigerator.
To serve, cut in 1/4-inch slices. Makes about 5 dozen.

title: italian potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan; cover with water. Bring to a boil and cook until tender; drain and cool. Peel and cube potatoes; place in a large bowl. Add dressing and toss to coat. Cover and chill for 2 hours. Add eggs, celery, onion, cucumber and green pepper; mix well.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients and roll on a floured surface.
Cut.
Place on a greased pan.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Makes 6 or 8 biscuits.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese together over very low heat, stirring often.
Sift together powdered sugar and cocoa.
Pour butter and cheese mixture over dry ingredients and beat well with a heavy-duty mixer.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 10 x 15-inch pan and refrigerate.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Have butcher cut chicken breasts, thighs or wings or a combination across the bone.
Marinate in teriyaki sauce for at least 1 hour.
Bake at 400° until almost all liquid has cooked away, approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.
This sauce can be used for pork or beef.

title: meat loaf barbecue style
directions: Mix well the beef, crumbs, egg, onion, salt and 1/2 can of tomato sauce. Form into loaf and place in 9 x 13 dish. Combine remaining 1 1/2 cans of tomato sauce with remaining ingredients to form sauce. Bake loaf at 350° until done, basting often with sauce.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
Lay onion rings on top.
Cover with mushroom soup and top with cheese.
Place in oven for a few minutes.

title: dinner on french bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except French bread together and simmer. Cut French bread in half lengthwise.
Stuff with meat mixture. Wrap in foil and bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Melt butter; add bell pepper and onion.
Add shrimp, soup. Ro-Tel tomatoes, salt, pepper and raw rice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: whole wheat, bran, raisin and date muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Set aside.
Stir together cereal and milk.
Let stand about 2 minutes. Add egg and shortening.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fill 12 greased 2 1/2-inch muffin cups (or use muffin liners).
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: pineapple salad delight(servings: 10)
directions: Combine juice drained from pineapple with enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Pour over gelatins; stir until dissolved.
Add salt.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: oat and bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Combine buttermilk, egg whites and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Stir in apples. Fill in greased muffin tins (or use papers) 1/3 full. Bake at 375° for 18 to 29 minutes.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into 1/2-cup freezer containers. Freeze fruit 8 hours.
Place frozen fruit servings in lunch boxes.
Fruit will thaw by lunchtime.
Yields 11 servings.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Pour melted butter into small cookie sheet.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over the butter, then add coconut, butterscotch chips and chocolate chips.
Dribble milk over pan and add nuts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: potato sourdough starter
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small mixing bowl.
Stir in warm water.
Cover with plastic wrap; pierce wrap 4 or 5 times with point of a sharp knife.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 days.

title: mother's salad dressing
directions: Shake together and refrigerate.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown a slice or two of bacon.
Slice up to give it flavor. Mix together and put on stove for 10 to 15 minutes on top of stove.

title: corn meal recipe
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Beat eggs and milk; pour in preheated pan and bake in 425° oven and stir.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Saute mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet. Remove from heat, stir in crabmeat, salt and pepper.
Set aside. Melt 1/4 cup butter, add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute stirring constantly.
Add cream and wine; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Stir in lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add crabmeat mixture and artichokes.
Spoon into a buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and sprinkle over crab mixture.
Bake, uncovered at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve with toast points.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Crumble together powdered sugar and peanut butter; set aside. Cook pudding according to directions on box.
Cool.

title: dirt pudding cheesecake
directions: Mix milk with pudding; set aside.
Crush Oreo cookies real fine and divide into two parts.
Add cream cheese and Cool Whip to pudding and beat 2 minutes.
Place 1/2 of crushed cookies into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add whipped mixture and place remaining crushed cookies on top.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine shortening, boiling water, sugar and salt.
Let cool. Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Beat egg and add to yeast mixture.
Pour yeast mixture into shortening mixture.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Cover and let rise until doubled (approximately 1 hour).
Punch dough down and knead.
Roll out on a lightly floured surface until the dough is approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into triangular shapes approximately 1-inch. Dip each piece in melted butter.
Drop into greased Bundt pan. Let rise approximately 1 hour in warm place.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool about 5 minutes.
Turn out onto a plate.

title: peanut candy
directions: Combine all ingredients in heavy saucepan, except peanuts. Cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water. Stir constantly to prevent scorching.
Turn onto a buttered baking sheet or wax paper.
When cool, cut into small squares.

title: banana yogurt frost
directions: Put ingredients in blender until smooth.
Makes three 9 ounce servings, 185 calories each.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except half of the cheese, and toss. Put other half of cheese on top.

title: ritza cheezza
directions: Beat egg and milk with fork.
Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Then dip pieces in egg mixture and roll in cracker crumbs.
Gently summersault chicken in broiler pan in which shortening previously has been melted.
Broil until golden brown, about 5 minutes, basting if necessary.
Broiling step is optional. Drain off any excess shortening.

title: squash dressing casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute lightly in butter.
Mash up squash with fork. Combine onion and butter mixture with slightly beaten eggs. Add cream of chicken soup (undiluted), squash, cornbread, salt and pepper.
Mix well and pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.

title: country coleslaw
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients well. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: butterscotch spiders
directions: Melt morsels over double boiler. Add noodles and nuts. Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: jacob's pancakes
directions: Mix together and put in microwave for 30 seconds.
Take out and let cool, but not much.

title: bacon and cheddar appetizers
directions: Fry and crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients well.
Place a spoonful of mixture on small breads.
Put in broiler until tops start to turn brown.

title: beef stroganoff(six to eight servings)
directions: Remove all fat and cut steaks into strips. In large plastic bag, combine 2 tablespoons flour and the salt; shake to mix.
Add steak; shake to coat.
In large skillet, melt butter over low heat.
Add steak.
Cook until brown over medium heat.

title: no-bake chocolate cake
directions: Prepare frosting in top of double boiler.
Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place over simmering water.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until thick and creamy.
Remove from over water.
Cool slightly.
Lay 3
graham crackers side by side on wax paper.
Cover crackers with frosting.
Repeat same step over. Reserve some of frosting for top and sides of cake.
Chill for 1 hour.
Your kids will love it.

title: unbaked chocolate cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk together.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and add pudding mix and rolled oats.
Mix together thoroughly.
Cool 15 minutes.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: easy chocolate fudge
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter or margarine; stir in regular chocolate pudding mix and add milk.
Heat to boiling; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Beat in sifted confectioners sugar.
Stir in vanilla.
Add chopped nuts.
Pour into buttered 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Garnish with walnut halves.
Chill fudge before cutting.
Makes 24 squares.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Stir in flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Slowly add cream and cook low until smooth.
Gradually add cheese and Worcestershire sauce; stir until cheese is melted.
Add crabmeat.
Place mixture in a greased baking dish and cover with crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef, drain off excess fat.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, onions, carrots, celery, barley, ketchup, bouillon, salt, basil and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Remove bay leaf.
Makes 10 cups.

title: chocolate chip banana bread
directions: Sift together four, soda and salt.
Mix in a separate bowl. Set aside.
Mix margarine and sugar in another bowl.
Add eggs and bananas to margarine and sugar mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients. Add chocolate chips.
Put in 2 loaf pans or 5 foil pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350 for loaf pans and foil pans at 350 for 40-50 minutes.

title: modified seven-layer salad
directions: Set aside 1 box of frozen peas and the grated carrots for garnish.

title: tabasco marinated shrimp
directions: Remove shells and veins from shrimp.
Rinse.
In a saucepan, combine beer, Tabasco sauce, salt, mustard, vinegar, onion slices, sugar and thyme.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 1 minute.
Add only enough cleaned shrimp as will be covered by the liquid mixture.
Return to boiling and then simmer 2 to 5 minutes, depending on size.
Remove shrimp and repeat cooking procedure. Remove from liquid.
Cool both shrimp and liquid.
Return shrimp to cooled liquid and marinate for several hours.
Drain.
Serve with wooden picks as hors d'oeuvres or appetizer.
Yields approximately 2 dozen.

title: aunt hortie's fudge
directions: Cook the sugar, milk and butter to rolling boil. Cook 5 more minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.
Add the chocolate chips and vanilla.
Beat until melted.
Pour into buttered 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: waving fish
directions: In a microwave-safe baking dish with a lid, lay snapper flat and cover with all the ingredients; place pats of butter on each fillet.
Cover and microwave 2 to 8 minutes, according to power of microwave.

title: oven-baked chicken(tastes like fried chicken without the calories)
directions: Wash and clean chicken.
Dip each piece of chicken into evaporated milk, then thoroughly coat with corn flake crumbs.
Put on cookie sheet and bake in a preheated 350° oven until done, approximately 1 hour.

title: coconut sour cream pound cake with fudge sauce
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the cake mix, sour cream, eggs, 1/2 cup sugar, oil, coconut flavoring and milk; beat for 2 full minutes with an electric mixer.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans or a 9 x 13-inch pan; pour in batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until it tests done; the cake will be very moist.
Let cool; place on serving dish and serve with warm sauce.

title: southern sweet potatoes
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients. Put in greased baking dish. Melt the 1/2 stick butter and cool.
Stir in the brown sugar, pecans and coconut. Sprinkle over the sweet potatoes. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes (thin) and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook butter, flour and milk until slightly thick.
Add cheese, salt, pepper, paprika, cayenne, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce and cook until heated through and thick.
Pour over potatoes and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; remove foil after 1/2 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Finish with 2% milk.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and reserve 1/3 cup liquid.
Fry sausage and onions.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients and top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy baked shrimp(4 servings)
directions: Tip:
Mix first 7 ingredients in a glass jar; shake well.

title: kahlua
directions: Dissolve coffee in 1/2 cup water.
Add to hot sugar water; bring to a boil.
Put vanilla bean and vodka in milk jug and add sugar mixture.
Set in fridge to age for a couple weeks.

title: goulash
directions: Cook onion in 1 or 2 tablespoons oil until turns clear; some will brown.
Put meat into onion and cook until meat is done. Drain. Add tomatoes, rice, beans, salt, pepper, chili powder and garlic powder.
If seems a little dry, add a cup of water or as much water as needed for simmering.
Simmer over low heat for about 30 minutes.

title: apple strudel
directions: Combine apples, sugar, cinnamon, raisins, almonds, rum and bread crumbs.
Let set 1 hour or overnight.
When the filling is ready, coat each phyllo leaf with butter and stack.
Work quickly, phyllo dries fast.
Add the filling down the center.
Bring in the sides and fold up, egg roll fashion.
Brush with melted butter and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: tink's generic pancakes
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Beat egg, add milk, then oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until blended, leaving batter a little lumpy.
Makes 10 to 12 medium pancakes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sifted sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and seasonings.
Blend well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Add flour mixture and beat. Blend in lemon extract.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 36 cookies.

title: oven fried perch with parmesan
directions: Dip fillets in milk.
Combine crumbs, Parmesan and thyme. Coat fish with bread crumbs.
Lay in single layer on greased, shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes per inch of thickness of the fish, measured at the thickest part or until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Saute onion in oil until golden.
Add egg and scramble mixture.
Stir in rice, soy sauce and diced meat. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serves four.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Make bread crumbs in blender (day old white bread without crust).
Mix crumbs, cheese, salt and parsley. Spread mixture in shallow pan.
Melt butter.
Add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Let cool.
Preheat oven to 350°. Dip chicken in butter mixture, then roll in crumbs. Pat on coating with hands.
Place chicken on large shallow baking sheet. Drizzle remainder of butter over chicken.
Bake until golden brown, 1 to 1 1/4 hours, basting once or twice.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients separately.
Combine milk and egg; stir in oil.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix. Pour in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices; blend.
Add eggs and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 50 minutes.
Can be made with cooked squash or sweet potatoes.

title: the best cheesecake
directions: Butter bottom of spring pan.
Crush graham crackers and sprinkle on bottom of pan.
Beat yolks, add sugar, cream cheese, sour cream, vanilla and flour.
Beat egg whites until very stiff. Fold into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes, then leave oven door open with cake inside to cool for 1 1/2 hours. Yum!
Yum!

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: snicker bar cake
directions: Combine wet ingredients in bowl.
Melt chocolate and add.
Mix well.
Combine dry ingredients and add slowly to wet.
Mix thoroughly each time.
Add Snicker bars last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use 8-inch layer cake pans, lightly greased.

title: spoon bread
directions: Put meal, salt, water and butter in pan and cook until thick. Beat eggs well. Add to milk and blend into meal mixture. Pour in baking dish. Bake 30 minutes in a 400° oven.
